WEBVTT

00:00:26.483 --> 00:00:28.489
SPEAKER:<i> You and I have lived
too long with this miracle</i>

00:00:29.400 --> 00:00:30.477
<i>to properly be appreciative.</i>

00:00:31.451 --> 00:00:33.457
{\an8}<i>Freedom is a fragile thing,</i>

00:00:33.468 --> 00:00:37.427
{\an8}<i>and it's never more
than one generation away from extinction.</i>

00:00:39.475 --> 00:00:42.408
<i>It is not ours by way of inheritance.</i>

00:00:44.405 --> 00:00:48.446
<i>It must be fought for and defended
constantly by each generation...</i>

00:00:51.409 --> 00:00:53.486
<i>for it comes only once to a people.</i>

00:00:56.426 --> 00:01:01.407
<i>And those in world history
who have known freedom and then lost it</i>

00:01:02.474 --> 00:01:04.421
<i>have never known it again.</i>

00:01:08.424 --> 00:01:10.487
For it will not be you speaking,

00:01:10.495 --> 00:01:15.475
but the Spirit of your Father
speaking through you."

00:01:46.491 --> 00:01:48.491
{\an8}SPOUSE: Mike, breakfast.

00:01:49.485 --> 00:01:52.462
{\an8}Sorry, honey. No time. Love you guys.

00:01:52.469 --> 00:01:54.478
Why can't you get my pancakes
to come out round?

00:01:54.486 --> 00:01:56.435
This one looks like Australia.

00:01:56.446 --> 00:01:59.452
They'll taste the same as any
other continent, sweetie, I promise.

00:01:59.463 --> 00:02:02.443
-Hey, Dad, what about this car?
-How much have you saved?

00:02:02.450 --> 00:02:03.765
Okay, well, if I sell my guitar,

00:02:03.789 --> 00:02:06.487
I can probably get a
couple hundred extra bucks.

00:02:06.497 --> 00:02:08.449
Yeah, it's too expensive.

00:02:08.460 --> 00:02:10.470
-MIKE: Just keep looking, all right?
-All right.

00:02:10.481 --> 00:02:12.400
-You're the best.
-(CHUCKLES)

00:02:12.411 --> 00:02:14.460
-I love you guys. I'll see you at 6:00.
-SPOUSE: Love you.

00:02:14.468 --> 00:02:15.487
(DOORBELL RINGS)

00:02:15.498 --> 00:02:17.454
(CHILDREN LAUGHING)

00:02:17.465 --> 00:02:18.464
Thanks.

00:02:18.471 --> 00:02:21.444
Reading and theology today.
Pickup at 5:00.

00:02:21.452 --> 00:02:22.451
Okay.

00:02:23.448 --> 00:02:24.471
Hey, Jackson.

00:02:26.489 --> 00:02:29.482
PARENT: Honey, I'll be home as soon
as work is over, okay?

00:02:31.406 --> 00:02:33.465
SPOUSE: I think Shannon has a new puzzle
she wants to show you.

00:02:33.473 --> 00:02:35.466
-Oh.
-Okay.

00:02:35.473 --> 00:02:36.486
SHANNON: Hey, Jackson's here.

00:02:36.496 --> 00:02:39.446
-Have you had breakfast yet?
-(CHUCKLES)

00:02:39.453 --> 00:02:42.433
Someone at the restaurant called in sick.
I'm gonna have to pull a double tonight.

00:02:42.440 --> 00:02:44.437
-(SPOUSE SIGHS) I'm sorry.
-It doesn't happen often.

00:02:44.447 --> 00:02:46.487
Anyway, Jackson's babysitter
will pick him up tonight.

00:02:46.497 --> 00:02:48.497
Do you remember Miss Meredith,
the church secretary?

00:02:49.404 --> 00:02:50.464
Taylor, it's gonna be fine.

00:02:50.471 --> 00:02:52.451
-Promise.
-Right.

00:02:52.458 --> 00:02:54.405
Thanks.

00:02:54.415 --> 00:02:55.498
This means more to us than you know.

00:03:02.409 --> 00:03:04.456
PERSON: This coffee is wonderful.

00:03:04.466 --> 00:03:06.409
PERSON 2: So, tell me
about your mission trip.

00:03:06.419 --> 00:03:08.449
-Was it amazing?
-Oh, you would love China.

00:03:08.456 --> 00:03:13.400
She's my native country,
but I don't think I can return.

00:03:13.407 --> 00:03:14.426
Why?

00:03:14.437 --> 00:03:18.410
The persecution of people of faith
is much worse now than when I left.

00:03:18.461 --> 00:03:22.424
And not just of Christians
but of Uyghur Muslims and others.

00:03:22.488 --> 00:03:26.411
Yeah, I heard they're trying
to detain millions in reeducation camps.

00:03:26.421 --> 00:03:28.458
Now they're trying
to contextualize the Bible

00:03:28.468 --> 00:03:31.438
to make it more culturally appropriate.

00:03:32.485 --> 00:03:34.485
Freedom is fragile, Ayisha.

00:03:35.442 --> 00:03:37.402
Did you see your family?

00:03:39.406 --> 00:03:41.439
I traveled to the other side of the world.

00:03:42.420 --> 00:03:44.486
They still won't speak to me
now that I'm a Christian.

00:03:44.493 --> 00:03:47.477
My family lives down the street,
and my father won't talk to me.

00:03:48.460 --> 00:03:50.460
I didn't think
that Christianity could be so...

00:03:51.447 --> 00:03:52.460
Lonely?

00:04:00.458 --> 00:04:02.491
Okay, this is North America.

00:04:02.498 --> 00:04:04.498
Put it where it belongs on the map.

00:04:05.409 --> 00:04:06.428
-(DOORBELL RINGS)
-(DOOR OPENS)

00:04:06.439 --> 00:04:08.425
Sorry I'm late.
Jail ministry went long.

00:04:08.432 --> 00:04:09.465
No worries.

00:04:11.416 --> 00:04:12.449
Hey, Brandon.

00:04:12.459 --> 00:04:14.426
-Hey, Mr. Hill.
-Oh, nice.

00:04:14.433 --> 00:04:16.482
Hey, calc now, cars later.

00:04:18.477 --> 00:04:21.424
-(WHISPERS) I like the truck.
-Yeah, me too.

00:04:22.494 --> 00:04:24.491
Seventeen, buying my first car.

00:04:24.497 --> 00:04:26.457
-I remember that.
-(CHUCKLES)

00:04:26.464 --> 00:04:28.434
It's amazing you can get him
to think about anything else.

00:04:28.444 --> 00:04:29.443
Yeah, I guess.

00:04:29.451 --> 00:04:30.498
(CHILDREN CHUCKLE)

00:04:31.408 --> 00:04:32.457
MR. HILL: How's Jackson doing?

00:04:32.465 --> 00:04:36.408
He's coming out of his shell a little bit.
He relaxes around Shannon, so that's good.

00:04:36.415 --> 00:04:37.498
Yeah. That is good.

00:04:38.462 --> 00:04:40.402
How about Taylor?

00:04:40.412 --> 00:04:41.478
She's been at the church for six months

00:04:41.486 --> 00:04:44.442
and I just realized that I don't know
anything about her.

00:04:44.449 --> 00:04:45.498
I guess that's my fault.

00:04:46.409 --> 00:04:49.400
No, don't beat yourself up.
She keeps to herself.

00:04:49.410 --> 00:04:51.479
Usually works nights so she can be
with Jackson during the day.

00:04:51.487 --> 00:04:53.466
I didn't know that.

00:04:53.477 --> 00:04:57.414
Still, it's my job to let people know
they have a home at St. Jude's.

00:04:57.477 --> 00:04:59.450
All right, everyone.

00:04:59.461 --> 00:05:02.487
Let's get our Bibles out and get ready
for some reading time.

00:05:02.498 --> 00:05:03.497
MR. HILL: Yeah, guys.

00:05:04.405 --> 00:05:05.434
Let's get to work.

00:05:05.445 --> 00:05:07.421
-CHILD: Yeah!
-(CHUCKLES)

00:05:07.478 --> 00:05:09.427
Today is... Drumroll, please.

00:05:10.472 --> 00:05:12.471
We're talking about Noah.

00:05:12.482 --> 00:05:14.498
Open your Bibles to Genesis 7.

00:05:23.423 --> 00:05:24.456
MR. HILL: That's really good, Shannon.

00:05:24.467 --> 00:05:26.473
Okay, let's talk about what we just heard.

00:05:26.483 --> 00:05:29.420
-It's about to get really wet.
-(CHILDREN CHUCKLES)

00:05:29.430 --> 00:05:31.467
Well, I think there's more
to this story than just rain.

00:05:31.474 --> 00:05:33.487
How do you think people reacted to Noah

00:05:33.498 --> 00:05:35.467
when he suddenly started
to build a big boat?

00:05:35.474 --> 00:05:37.430
-They probably thought he was nuts.
-(KNOCKING)

00:05:37.438 --> 00:05:40.408
MR. HILL: I think you may be right.
And that's the point.

00:05:40.418 --> 00:05:43.415
Sometimes trusting God
means believing and doing things

00:05:43.422 --> 00:05:45.405
that the world won't understand.

00:05:45.465 --> 00:05:48.449
But we know that God honors
our obedience to him.

00:05:50.422 --> 00:05:52.409
I'm Ms. Dowd with Social Services.

00:05:52.419 --> 00:05:55.432
I'm here to review
your homeschooling environment.

00:05:56.466 --> 00:05:58.476
Uh, no one called to let me know.

00:05:58.487 --> 00:06:00.499
We've switched to unannounced visitations.

00:06:03.457 --> 00:06:05.427
May I come in?

00:06:09.471 --> 00:06:10.487
MS. DOWD: Good afternoon, children.

00:06:11.468 --> 00:06:13.474
-Good afternoon.
-JACKSON: Good afternoon.

00:06:13.485 --> 00:06:15.425
I am Ms. Dowd.

00:06:16.412 --> 00:06:18.418
Since you don't have
a board-certified instructor,

00:06:18.425 --> 00:06:20.428
I'm here to make sure
you aren't missing anything.

00:06:21.472 --> 00:06:24.492
Is Ms. short for miss or missus?

00:06:25.403 --> 00:06:26.422
(CHUCKLES)

00:06:27.423 --> 00:06:30.422
It's not short for anything.
It's complete by itself.

00:06:30.430 --> 00:06:31.453
She meant no disrespect.

00:06:31.460 --> 00:06:33.459
She's just asking
if you're single or married

00:06:33.470 --> 00:06:35.447
so she might address you properly.

00:06:37.491 --> 00:06:39.481
I identify as self-partnered.

00:06:41.491 --> 00:06:44.438
Might I ask what subject we're studying?

00:06:44.445 --> 00:06:47.454
Uh, it's a combined unit
of reading and theology.

00:06:47.462 --> 00:06:48.481
And you are?

00:06:48.492 --> 00:06:50.494
Oh, I'm Reverend David Hill
from St. Jude's.

00:06:51.405 --> 00:06:53.442
Our church helped found the co-op.

00:06:53.449 --> 00:06:57.415
My interest is only with the parents
and with the children.

00:06:57.479 --> 00:07:00.459
And the lesson plan is the Bible.

00:07:01.473 --> 00:07:05.417
Well, for theology, I'd be hard-pressed
to find a more appropriate book.

00:07:07.460 --> 00:07:08.480
Uh-huh.

00:07:14.408 --> 00:07:16.431
Why don't you continue
as if I'm not even here?

00:07:17.424 --> 00:07:18.423
DAVID: Okay.

00:07:18.431 --> 00:07:20.425
You wanna pick up
where we left off, Shannon?

00:07:20.431 --> 00:07:21.430
Sure.

00:07:22.412 --> 00:07:25.481
You are to bring into the ark
two of all living creatures,

00:07:25.492 --> 00:07:28.429
male and female,
to keep them alive with you.

00:07:29.432 --> 00:07:32.409
Noah did everything
as God commanded him."

00:07:32.416 --> 00:07:37.493
So the takeaway, their teachable moment
from the Noah myth, is obey God or die?

00:07:39.403 --> 00:07:41.453
(CHUCKLES) I mean,
that's one way to look at it.

00:07:41.464 --> 00:07:42.463
Uh-huh.

00:07:43.484 --> 00:07:44.483
And the animals.

00:07:45.454 --> 00:07:48.430
What exactly was the sin
that required their destruction?

00:07:49.488 --> 00:07:51.404
(SIGHS)

00:07:53.401 --> 00:07:55.428
These are my recommendations to the state.

00:07:58.415 --> 00:08:00.452
-Escalation?
-That's not up to me.

00:08:04.496 --> 00:08:07.499
(DOOR OPENS, CLOSES)

00:08:20.498 --> 00:08:22.424
(ENGINE OFF)

00:08:29.452 --> 00:08:31.404
I heard you pulling up.

00:08:32.439 --> 00:08:33.451
Long day, huh?

00:08:33.459 --> 00:08:35.432
Very. How was Jackson?

00:08:35.439 --> 00:08:38.455
You know I love your boy
like he's my own,

00:08:39.466 --> 00:08:41.472
but he needs help, Taylor.

00:09:02.485 --> 00:09:04.411
Mommy.

00:09:04.422 --> 00:09:05.458
It's okay, honey.

00:09:05.469 --> 00:09:06.468
I'm here.

00:09:06.475 --> 00:09:08.472
You came back.

00:09:08.479 --> 00:09:10.405
Of course.

00:09:10.469 --> 00:09:14.403
Mommy always comes back.
I was just at work.

00:09:14.410 --> 00:09:18.403
What if you had to go to heaven
to be with Daddy?

00:09:21.470 --> 00:09:25.443
Honey, that's not gonna happen.

00:09:27.498 --> 00:09:29.444
(SIGHS)

00:09:37.489 --> 00:09:40.429
PERSON:<i> The country is just now
beginning to realize</i>

00:09:40.439 --> 00:09:42.498
{\an8}<i>that unity means winning under our terms.</i>

00:09:43.409 --> 00:09:45.458
{\an8}<i>Frankly,
everybody's tired of this stalemate.</i>

00:09:45.466 --> 00:09:50.415
<i>The very idea of unity in this country
we now consider to be a myth.</i>

00:09:50.426 --> 00:09:52.460
<i>Everybody's ready to move on
from this gridlock,</i>

00:09:52.467 --> 00:09:56.433
<i>which is why my staff and I
have drafted new legislation.</i>

00:09:57.400 --> 00:10:00.444
<i>Legislation that's gonna guarantee
that every child in this country</i>

00:10:00.451 --> 00:10:03.400
<i>gets the kind of education
that they deserve.</i>

00:10:03.494 --> 00:10:06.461
<i>Now mind you, we're gonna get this done</i>

00:10:06.468 --> 00:10:10.414
<i>with or without the help of our friends
from across the aisle.</i>

00:10:10.425 --> 00:10:12.452
<i>We know what the American people need.</i>

00:10:12.462 --> 00:10:15.499
<i>They need progress,
and we're gonna give it to them.</i>

00:10:16.409 --> 00:10:17.475
<i>Thank you.</i>

00:10:34.418 --> 00:10:37.451
Remember the visit we got
from Social Services the other day,

00:10:37.461 --> 00:10:39.451
and we thought
it wasn't gonna be a big deal?

00:10:39.461 --> 00:10:41.405
Yeah?

00:10:41.415 --> 00:10:43.464
It is a big deal. (SIGHS)

00:10:48.412 --> 00:10:50.411
(DAVID SIGHS) I know, Mike.

00:10:50.419 --> 00:10:52.416
Phone's been ringing off the hook here.

00:10:53.469 --> 00:10:55.482
-Yeah.
-Look, I'll come by later, okay?

00:10:55.490 --> 00:10:57.466
We'll figure this out together.

00:10:58.417 --> 00:10:59.416
Yeah, bye.

00:11:00.447 --> 00:11:01.446
Oh, hey, you two.

00:11:02.417 --> 00:11:05.433
I'm here to pick up those study guides
for seminary school,

00:11:05.497 --> 00:11:07.484
but we can come back if this is a bad time.

00:11:07.491 --> 00:11:10.440
No, no, no, no, no, please,
come on in. Have a seat.

00:11:11.401 --> 00:11:12.454
-Uh, Meredith, can you find those?
-Yeah.

00:11:12.465 --> 00:11:13.474
(SIGHS)

00:11:14.468 --> 00:11:16.471
Martin, you're gonna be a great pastor.

00:11:17.448 --> 00:11:19.439
What's the latest
on the homeschooling co-op?

00:11:19.449 --> 00:11:23.415
Well, every family in the co-op
has just received a court summons.

00:11:23.422 --> 00:11:25.416
-How is that possible?
-DAVID: I don't know.

00:11:25.423 --> 00:11:28.456
I always thought the law gave parents
the freedom to homeschool as they see fit.

00:11:28.466 --> 00:11:30.449
Growing up,
we always heard that in America

00:11:30.456 --> 00:11:33.473
you could say whatever you please,
wear whatever you like

00:11:33.483 --> 00:11:35.427
and worship whomever you will.

00:11:35.437 --> 00:11:37.467
And that's still true, Ayisha.

00:11:37.474 --> 00:11:40.444
This is just a misunderstanding.
It has to be.

00:11:40.454 --> 00:11:43.444
Yes, the Supreme Court
said we can worship God

00:11:43.454 --> 00:11:45.467
according to the dictates
of our own conscience.

00:11:46.428 --> 00:11:48.408
It's how the court defines liberty.

00:11:48.478 --> 00:11:50.484
How do you know so much
about the Constitution?

00:11:50.492 --> 00:11:53.455
I studied for the civics test
to get my citizenship.

00:11:53.462 --> 00:11:55.461
American history is a hobby for me now.

00:11:55.472 --> 00:11:56.471
(BOTH CHUCKLE)

00:11:56.479 --> 00:11:58.492
The Constitution is an amazing document.

00:11:59.403 --> 00:12:02.412
Ah. Yup, I suppose it is.

00:12:02.423 --> 00:12:03.429
(AYISHA CHUCKLES)

00:12:11.411 --> 00:12:13.457
Uh, hi, excuse me.
Are you selling your car?

00:12:13.464 --> 00:12:15.497
Sure am. You buying?

00:12:16.474 --> 00:12:18.447
Yeah. Yeah, yeah. Uh, well, maybe.

00:12:19.415 --> 00:12:20.438
Um...

00:12:20.488 --> 00:12:22.441
-I'm Brandon.
-Kayla.

00:12:23.425 --> 00:12:24.488
So, like what you see?

00:12:25.459 --> 00:12:26.458
Huh?

00:12:27.425 --> 00:12:28.438
The car.

00:12:29.429 --> 00:12:33.409
(CHUCKLES) Yes. Yeah.
Um, she's very beautiful.

00:12:33.416 --> 00:12:35.415
-(CHUCKLES)
-It's beautiful.

00:12:35.426 --> 00:12:36.479
-The car, I was talking about.
-Uh-huh.

00:12:36.490 --> 00:12:39.449
-Right.
-This is just temporary right now.

00:12:39.460 --> 00:12:42.447
-May I ask why you're selling it?
-I start college in the fall.

00:12:42.457 --> 00:12:44.463
It's too expensive to have a car on campus.

00:12:44.474 --> 00:12:46.476
Totally, college. Yeah.

00:12:46.484 --> 00:12:50.428
Well, it'd be great
if I could get some pictures or...

00:12:51.498 --> 00:12:54.431
Uh, yeah. Brandon.

00:12:54.442 --> 00:12:55.441
-Kayla.
-Yeah.

00:12:55.448 --> 00:12:57.411
-I already asked you.
-Yup. (CHUCKLES)

00:12:58.412 --> 00:12:59.431
Sorry.

00:13:12.477 --> 00:13:14.450
It all seems so extreme.

00:13:14.460 --> 00:13:18.400
Dave, I want you to know that we will not
be cooperating at all, okay?

00:13:18.411 --> 00:13:20.480
-Yeah. Not giving in is more like it.
-MIKE: Yeah.

00:13:20.487 --> 00:13:22.484
I've spoken to the board.

00:13:22.494 --> 00:13:26.414
We could certainly adjust the curriculum
to be more accommodating.

00:13:26.421 --> 00:13:29.484
Don't you mean compromise the curriculum?
We already told them we're not conforming.

00:13:29.495 --> 00:13:32.415
Religion has been removed
from our schools.

00:13:32.422 --> 00:13:35.402
They're teaching kids
that they don't need God.

00:13:35.469 --> 00:13:38.445
That faith is irrelevant
to their personal choices, Dave.

00:13:38.453 --> 00:13:39.479
DAVID: I hear you.

00:13:39.486 --> 00:13:42.456
I mean, these are some of the reasons
we started the co-op in the first place.

00:13:42.466 --> 00:13:43.465
It's just...

00:13:45.437 --> 00:13:46.483
I need you to understand

00:13:46.490 --> 00:13:49.406
what you're getting yourself into
when you fight City Hall.

00:13:49.417 --> 00:13:51.480
DAVID:<i> The church really should've
moved off-campus 50 years ago...</i>

00:13:51.487 --> 00:13:54.440
<i>Court costs, attorney fees.</i>

00:13:54.451 --> 00:13:56.431
Communities become divided.

00:13:56.438 --> 00:13:58.485
<i>A beacon of violence and controversy,</i>

00:13:58.491 --> 00:14:02.435
<i>-and it has no place here...</i>
-You're under arrest.

00:14:02.442 --> 00:14:04.475
<i>...at Hadley University campus.</i>

00:14:10.422 --> 00:14:13.475
It's a time-consuming, draining experience

00:14:14.466 --> 00:14:16.489
that rarely ends
the way that you had hoped.

00:14:19.467 --> 00:14:20.486
(SIGHS)

00:14:21.494 --> 00:14:24.456
We understand. (CLEARS THROAT)

00:14:24.467 --> 00:14:26.473
DAVID: Let me know
if there's anything else I can do.

00:14:27.427 --> 00:14:29.440
Sorry I couldn't be of more help.

00:14:31.451 --> 00:14:33.461
MS. DOWD:
During our observed instruction,

00:14:33.471 --> 00:14:35.444
a number of deficiencies were noted.

00:14:35.455 --> 00:14:39.425
These include: one,
lack of instructional effectiveness,

00:14:39.435 --> 00:14:43.476
two, an environment inferior
to a group-learning experience,

00:14:43.486 --> 00:14:48.445
three, the parents' inability
to cover all intellectual areas,

00:14:48.456 --> 00:14:51.469
and four, the absence of
sufficient equipment,

00:14:51.477 --> 00:14:53.453
especially in the sciences.

00:14:53.460 --> 00:14:57.426
We are concerned that these children
may not acquire the essential skills

00:14:57.437 --> 00:15:00.403
for good citizenship
and for their learning.

00:15:00.411 --> 00:15:02.480
{\an8}Has there been some attempt
at upgrading the curriculum?

00:15:02.491 --> 00:15:04.428
{\an8}There has, Your Honor.

00:15:04.438 --> 00:15:05.471
{\an8}But the parents in the St. Jude co-op

00:15:05.478 --> 00:15:09.455
have refused to conform their curriculum
with district norms.

00:15:09.462 --> 00:15:10.478
Is this true?

00:15:10.488 --> 00:15:13.475
Yes, Your Honor,
but you need to understand--

00:15:13.482 --> 00:15:16.455
A simple "yes" or "no"
would answer the question.

00:15:16.462 --> 00:15:18.496
If you say "yes," that's a problem.

00:15:19.406 --> 00:15:21.405
Does the district have a recommendation?

00:15:21.413 --> 00:15:22.462
We recommend the children be returned

00:15:22.473 --> 00:15:24.496
to an accredited learning program
immediately.

00:15:25.407 --> 00:15:26.450
(CLEARS THROAT) Your Honor,

00:15:26.460 --> 00:15:28.497
the district is complaining
about the lack of socialization.

00:15:29.407 --> 00:15:30.459
But our children
are being denied the chance

00:15:30.467 --> 00:15:33.490
to participate in any kind of
extracurricular activities--

00:15:33.497 --> 00:15:34.496
State law is clear.

00:15:35.408 --> 00:15:38.474
Homeschoolers have no right
to exploit extracurricular activities

00:15:38.481 --> 00:15:40.447
at a school they don't see fit to attend.

00:15:40.458 --> 00:15:42.468
It's an either/or situation, Mr. McKinnon.

00:15:42.478 --> 00:15:45.445
The children in your co-op
cannot ask for dessert

00:15:45.452 --> 00:15:47.432
without eating their dinner first.

00:15:47.442 --> 00:15:49.445
DAVID: Their parents
pay taxes though, right?

00:15:50.432 --> 00:15:51.435
Excuse me?

00:15:51.446 --> 00:15:53.445
I mean, their property taxes.

00:15:54.426 --> 00:15:57.420
That would cover the dessert
and the dinner too, correct?

00:15:57.430 --> 00:15:59.482
-And you are?
-Reverend David Hill, Your Honor.

00:15:59.493 --> 00:16:01.493
It was our church
that organized the co-op.

00:16:02.487 --> 00:16:05.410
I remember you well, Pastor.

00:16:05.417 --> 00:16:08.447
I do not pretend to be
an educational professional,

00:16:08.454 --> 00:16:11.471
and I also note, however,
that neither are any of you.

00:16:12.448 --> 00:16:14.454
This case could take years to settle,

00:16:14.465 --> 00:16:16.481
and your children simply
can't wait that long.

00:16:16.488 --> 00:16:19.455
In the interim,
I am going to sign an order

00:16:19.465 --> 00:16:22.418
giving you ten days to either conform

00:16:22.429 --> 00:16:24.482
to the district supervisor's recommendation

00:16:24.489 --> 00:16:28.406
or enroll your children
in accredited schools.

00:16:28.473 --> 00:16:30.432
And if we refuse?

00:16:31.457 --> 00:16:32.469
(SIGHS)

00:16:32.480 --> 00:16:35.456
Parents have the freedom
to raise their children

00:16:35.467 --> 00:16:38.480
in line with their moral
and religious beliefs.

00:16:38.487 --> 00:16:42.450
Your children, however,
enjoy the right to an education.

00:16:42.458 --> 00:16:47.488
Your freedoms as parents do not
supersede your children's rights.

00:16:48.455 --> 00:16:49.468
Your Honor, please--

00:16:49.475 --> 00:16:52.481
Your beliefs do not exempt you
from the law, Mr. McKinnon.

00:16:52.489 --> 00:16:56.476
Therefore, if your children do not show up
at school a week from Monday,

00:16:56.486 --> 00:17:00.459
you will be fined $1,000 a day
for the first two weeks.

00:17:00.469 --> 00:17:04.406
Thereafter, you will be charged
with contempt of court,

00:17:04.416 --> 00:17:05.493
meaning you will be incarcerated.

00:17:06.403 --> 00:17:07.440
During which time

00:17:07.450 --> 00:17:10.487
the court will appoint temporary custody
of your children

00:17:10.494 --> 00:17:14.440
to someone who will abide
by the court's decision.

00:17:14.451 --> 00:17:17.441
Perhaps the good reverend
can explain further

00:17:17.451 --> 00:17:20.488
the ramifications of contempt
in this courtroom.

00:17:21.468 --> 00:17:22.484
So ordered.

00:17:26.459 --> 00:17:28.472
-(THUNDER RUMBLING)
-AYISHA: Just tell me, Lord,

00:17:29.459 --> 00:17:32.496
is my family's isolation the price
that you're asking me to pay?

00:17:37.436 --> 00:17:40.453
Of course I'll abide by your will,
whatever that may be, but...

00:17:43.427 --> 00:17:45.474
if there's any other way,
just please show me.

00:17:48.421 --> 00:17:50.423
(SOBS) I'll do anything...

00:17:52.421 --> 00:17:54.441
if I could just see my family again.

00:17:55.478 --> 00:17:58.405
-(THUNDER RUMBLING)
-(RAIN FALLING)

00:18:27.451 --> 00:18:29.418
(SIGHS)

00:18:30.435 --> 00:18:31.494
(THUNDER RUMBLES)

00:18:32.402 --> 00:18:34.428
Uh, excuse me, Pastor Hill?

00:18:34.435 --> 00:18:35.469
Jude.

00:18:36.442 --> 00:18:37.491
I told you, just call me David.

00:18:37.499 --> 00:18:39.479
Oh... (CHUCKLES)... right.

00:18:39.486 --> 00:18:42.435
Hey, you know what?
Maybe you can help me with this sermon.

00:18:42.446 --> 00:18:43.493
Certainly, Pastor David.

00:18:44.400 --> 00:18:45.433
Ah...

00:18:45.443 --> 00:18:47.420
-Okay.
-What's the topic?

00:18:47.430 --> 00:18:50.446
Topic is, "What does faith look like?"

00:18:50.454 --> 00:18:53.401
It's so hard to nail it down.

00:18:53.411 --> 00:18:55.477
(CHUCKLES) Yes, because it's relative.

00:18:57.438 --> 00:19:00.421
In Nigeria, many of the people
that were ministered to

00:19:00.431 --> 00:19:02.487
are only ever a moment away from death.

00:19:03.455 --> 00:19:07.495
Death from hunger, disease, bad water.

00:19:08.462 --> 00:19:11.465
Villagers walk to church, many for hours.

00:19:12.436 --> 00:19:15.416
They don't say,
Oh, I have to go to church today.

00:19:16.446 --> 00:19:20.406
They say, "Yes, it's Sunday.
I get to go to church."

00:19:20.417 --> 00:19:23.404
In the backcountry,
people don't have money.

00:19:23.484 --> 00:19:27.437
They bring carrots, eggs, milk.

00:19:27.447 --> 00:19:28.497
It's all they have.

00:19:29.498 --> 00:19:31.434
It's their widow's mite.

00:19:32.405 --> 00:19:36.492
They're happy to give the Lord thanks
for one more week of life.

00:19:37.458 --> 00:19:40.414
So when somebody
puts a gun on their heads and says,

00:19:40.422 --> 00:19:41.498
Denounce Jesus and die,

00:19:42.492 --> 00:19:46.426
they say, "Jesus, I'm coming home to you."

00:19:47.469 --> 00:19:51.483
That's what faith looks like
for those who have nothing,

00:19:51.490 --> 00:19:57.470
who are so close to death every day
and still have that fire and love for God.

00:20:01.437 --> 00:20:02.484
You humble me, Jude.

00:20:02.491 --> 00:20:03.493
Nah.

00:20:04.404 --> 00:20:05.491
We all have our cross to bear.

00:20:07.401 --> 00:20:11.401
America is a country
so blessed with prosperity,

00:20:12.412 --> 00:20:16.422
it only makes sense
that much will be asked of her in return.

00:20:17.486 --> 00:20:22.463
To whom much is given,
much will be required.

00:20:24.493 --> 00:20:26.487
Much will be required.

00:20:30.454 --> 00:20:31.494
(THUNDER RUMBLES)

00:20:37.421 --> 00:20:39.408
I miss you, old friend.

00:20:48.405 --> 00:20:49.489
(PHONE RINGING)

00:20:53.416 --> 00:20:54.442
(SNIFFLES)

00:20:55.443 --> 00:20:57.459
Uh, St. Jude's Church. (SIGHS)

00:20:58.410 --> 00:20:59.440
Yeah, this is he.

00:21:03.414 --> 00:21:04.426
Uh, okay.

00:21:05.407 --> 00:21:06.413
Wait, what?

00:21:08.441 --> 00:21:09.474
Who is this again?

00:21:09.488 --> 00:21:11.467
PARENT: I don't have the money
to pay for those kinds of fines.

00:21:11.478 --> 00:21:13.430
None of us do.

00:21:13.441 --> 00:21:15.481
Well, that's it. We're gonna enroll
our kids into Oakwood on Monday.

00:21:15.492 --> 00:21:17.415
Look at this.

00:21:17.425 --> 00:21:18.484
You know the Andersons, right?

00:21:18.495 --> 00:21:20.485
Okay, all their kids go to Oakwood.

00:21:20.495 --> 00:21:23.436
Matty Anderson brought that
home from school.

00:21:24.452 --> 00:21:27.402
This is an advertisement
for birth control.

00:21:27.413 --> 00:21:28.412
Yeah.

00:21:28.420 --> 00:21:29.493
They passed it out in class.

00:21:30.400 --> 00:21:32.476
Matty's in the second grade.
He's seven.

00:21:32.483 --> 00:21:34.432
How long till they bring that here?

00:21:34.443 --> 00:21:37.450
We're not subjecting Shannon to that
and none of you should have to.

00:21:37.460 --> 00:21:39.447
DAVID: No, you shouldn't...

00:21:40.447 --> 00:21:43.453
which is why I think we should fight this.

00:21:44.464 --> 00:21:45.477
We need to.

00:21:46.481 --> 00:21:51.405
With all due respect, Dave,
you're not the one on the hook for fines.

00:21:51.415 --> 00:21:52.485
Not to mention,
the contempt of court.

00:21:54.472 --> 00:21:57.416
The church will stand with you on this.

00:21:57.422 --> 00:21:58.421
We'll organize a plan

00:21:58.433 --> 00:22:00.495
and help with any court costs
and attorney fees if need be.

00:22:01.403 --> 00:22:04.433
Dave, the church doesn't have
those kinds of funds.

00:22:05.483 --> 00:22:07.486
We have eight days to figure it out.

00:22:09.404 --> 00:22:10.430
And I...

00:22:11.467 --> 00:22:15.454
I will personally cover the cost
of any fines if we have to.

00:22:16.448 --> 00:22:17.883
David, unless you won the lottery,

00:22:17.907 --> 00:22:20.421
there's no way you'll
be able to pay for all this.

00:22:20.431 --> 00:22:22.404
Unless you're betting you won't have to.

00:22:22.415 --> 00:22:24.474
I have faith that I won't have to.

00:22:24.485 --> 00:22:27.472
And if I do, I'll deal with it then.

00:22:27.482 --> 00:22:29.408
This is important.

00:22:30.419 --> 00:22:31.442
Why the change of heart?

00:22:31.452 --> 00:22:33.449
(CHUCKLES)

00:22:33.456 --> 00:22:39.419
An old friend reminded me
that our freedoms came with a price.

00:22:40.453 --> 00:22:42.420
China banned homeschooling

00:22:42.427 --> 00:22:46.476
because homeschool students are not
exposed to state-sponsored indoctrination.

00:22:46.487 --> 00:22:47.486
Mmm.

00:22:47.494 --> 00:22:51.474
If any parent chooses to homeschool,
they must do so underground

00:22:51.485 --> 00:22:53.421
and at great risk.

00:22:53.485 --> 00:22:58.401
Once a freedom is taken away,
it is very difficult to get it back.

00:22:58.408 --> 00:22:59.407
DAVID: Exactly.

00:22:59.419 --> 00:23:02.471
And to that end,
I think we might have a little help.

00:23:02.479 --> 00:23:07.412
Earlier, I got a phone call from
Daryl Smith, a congressman from Texas.

00:23:07.423 --> 00:23:08.422
Congressman?

00:23:08.430 --> 00:23:10.459
Mr. Smith told me
Congress is meeting next week,

00:23:10.470 --> 00:23:12.479
and they're having hearings on education.

00:23:12.490 --> 00:23:16.430
They asked if any of us would go
to Washington and describe our situation.

00:23:18.474 --> 00:23:20.404
Washington, DC?

00:23:20.464 --> 00:23:22.407
Washington, DC.

00:23:22.414 --> 00:23:23.470
-You okay?
-Yeah.

00:23:28.478 --> 00:23:30.422
Hey, son, make sure to help Grandma.

00:23:30.428 --> 00:23:31.477
It's only gonna be a couple nights,
I promise.

00:23:31.489 --> 00:23:33.408
Yeah, sure.

00:23:34.432 --> 00:23:36.488
Hey, Dad, I know with everything going on,
money might be tight,

00:23:36.496 --> 00:23:38.498
especially if you guys have to pay fines.

00:23:39.409 --> 00:23:41.425
Everything's gonna be fine.
We're gonna work this out.

00:23:41.433 --> 00:23:42.459
What's this?

00:23:42.466 --> 00:23:45.450
Well, just in case,
I want you to take the money for the car.

00:23:45.460 --> 00:23:48.433
It's not gonna kill me
to ride a bike a little while longer.

00:23:48.444 --> 00:23:50.443
You're gonna make me cry now, okay? No.

00:23:51.410 --> 00:23:53.466
Me and your mother
are gonna work this thing out, I promise.

00:23:53.477 --> 00:23:55.474
But you know,
I want you to know something, okay?

00:23:55.481 --> 00:23:59.430
I couldn't be any more proud
than I am of you right now, son.

00:23:59.441 --> 00:24:00.440
(CHUCKLES)

00:24:00.448 --> 00:24:02.424
-I love you, man.
-Yeah, I love you.

00:24:03.428 --> 00:24:04.475
All right, don't cry. Don't cry.

00:24:04.482 --> 00:24:08.431
Be good for Grandma, do whatever she says,
and no arguing over bedtime, okay?

00:24:08.442 --> 00:24:09.486
Mom, really?

00:24:09.496 --> 00:24:11.432
I got this.

00:24:11.442 --> 00:24:13.436
You too big to give your mom a hug?

00:24:14.476 --> 00:24:17.436
MIKE: You guys heard from Taylor?
We need to get going.

00:24:17.446 --> 00:24:18.469
-(CAR APPROACHES)
-There she is.

00:24:20.447 --> 00:24:22.446
(ENGINE OFF)

00:24:26.454 --> 00:24:27.497
I hope I haven't made us late.

00:24:28.404 --> 00:24:29.460
What's wrong, honey?
Is it Jackson?

00:24:29.468 --> 00:24:31.404
He's with Miss Meredith.

00:24:31.471 --> 00:24:32.484
It's worth it, right?

00:24:32.495 --> 00:24:34.461
-Our kids?
-Of course it is.

00:24:34.468 --> 00:24:37.481
-Taylor, what's the matter?
-We should go. We can't miss our plane.

00:24:40.422 --> 00:24:42.495
DAVID: I really appreciate you
coming along and keeping me company.

00:24:43.402 --> 00:24:46.429
Did you know that two presidents
kept alligators at the White House?

00:24:46.436 --> 00:24:48.473
It's just sometimes
I feel a little out of place

00:24:48.483 --> 00:24:50.446
being the only non-parent in the group.

00:24:50.453 --> 00:24:51.455
No way.

00:24:51.466 --> 00:24:52.486
I know, it's silly, but--

00:24:52.497 --> 00:24:56.463
There's a statue of Darth Vader's head
on top of the National Cathedral.

00:24:56.470 --> 00:24:58.423
-What?
-What?

00:24:59.437 --> 00:25:02.454
Oh, thanks for letting me come along.
It means a lot to me.

00:25:02.464 --> 00:25:04.484
Ah, don't mention it.

00:25:13.439 --> 00:25:17.405
Hey, what do you think of this car?

00:25:19.426 --> 00:25:21.406
That's freedom right there.

00:25:21.416 --> 00:25:23.415
It's a chance to hang
with people my own age.

00:25:23.423 --> 00:25:24.436
What car?

00:25:24.443 --> 00:25:26.426
I see some girl, and...

00:25:26.437 --> 00:25:27.493
Oh, wait, there it is.

00:25:28.403 --> 00:25:29.426
Are those the wheels?

00:25:29.437 --> 00:25:31.417
You're so funny. Yeah.

00:25:31.424 --> 00:25:33.421
What do you know?
You're just a fifth-grader.

00:25:33.427 --> 00:25:37.473
I know Mom and Dad will be mad
if you waste your money on the wrong car.

00:25:37.484 --> 00:25:39.451
Okay, what? It's a great car.

00:25:40.418 --> 00:25:41.494
(KAYLA CHUCKLES)

00:25:42.405 --> 00:25:45.408
All in one piece. Okay, got it.

00:25:45.419 --> 00:25:46.468
(ENGINE OFF)

00:25:46.475 --> 00:25:47.485
Thanks for this.

00:25:47.492 --> 00:25:49.489
I know you're gonna be very happy
with the car.

00:25:49.496 --> 00:25:52.402
No, um, thank you.

00:25:52.409 --> 00:25:56.486
I can finally give the bike to my sister
and travel in style.

00:26:02.424 --> 00:26:06.457
So, um, can I, uh, ask you a question?

00:26:07.437 --> 00:26:08.436
Okay.

00:26:08.444 --> 00:26:10.403
(CHUCKLES) I just gotta be real with you.

00:26:10.411 --> 00:26:15.407
Um, I mean, this is my first car and all.
I look a little older than my age.

00:26:15.415 --> 00:26:16.448
-Um...
-(CHUCKLES)

00:26:16.458 --> 00:26:19.488
You know, it's a big step of my life
and, well, I was just kinda wondering--

00:26:19.495 --> 00:26:21.411
If it's a good car?

00:26:23.422 --> 00:26:24.421
Yeah.

00:26:24.429 --> 00:26:27.462
It's actually an awesome car.

00:26:27.473 --> 00:26:30.406
-(SIGHS)
-I'd take her with me if I could.

00:26:30.476 --> 00:26:31.475
That's great.

00:26:32.440 --> 00:26:35.456
Yeah, that's, um, really good to know.

00:26:44.458 --> 00:26:48.484
Well, so I guess you'll
be leaving for State in the fall.

00:26:48.495 --> 00:26:52.401
Yeah, my last little hurrah
before I have to start adulting.

00:26:52.412 --> 00:26:55.449
Yeah. Well, I was just thinking--

00:26:55.459 --> 00:26:57.496
-Hey, sorry, um, this is my mom.
-(PHONE VIBRATING)

00:26:58.402 --> 00:27:00.458
-I kinda have to take it.
-Yeah, yeah, of course.

00:27:00.466 --> 00:27:01.465
Hey, Mom.

00:27:02.430 --> 00:27:04.492
Um, yeah, I'm here with the boy
who bought my car.

00:27:06.460 --> 00:27:09.466
It's fine. I can fend for myself.

00:27:11.447 --> 00:27:15.417
Yeah, I'll just throw something
in the microwave, I guess.

00:27:16.498 --> 00:27:18.410
(ENGINE STARTS)

00:27:19.418 --> 00:27:22.448
Um, yeah. Okay, Mom. Got it.

00:28:06.476 --> 00:28:08.439
(LINE RINGING)

00:28:10.410 --> 00:28:11.422
(PHONE BEEPS)

00:28:11.473 --> 00:28:12.499
Hi, Baba, it's me.

00:28:13.473 --> 00:28:18.454
I just wanted to call to tell you
that I love you and I miss you.

00:28:19.427 --> 00:28:21.440
<i>I really wish that you would talk to me.</i>

00:28:25.411 --> 00:28:27.460
(AYISHA SIGHS)
<i>Please call me.</i>

00:28:41.463 --> 00:28:43.443
DAVID: It's still early.
You guys wanna grab a bite?

00:28:43.453 --> 00:28:45.419
How about touring the city?

00:28:45.470 --> 00:28:48.419
Uh, guys, I don't think
Taylor's gonna wanna do any sightseeing.

00:28:48.427 --> 00:28:52.407
On the flight over here, she told us
that she was released from her job.

00:28:52.457 --> 00:28:53.456
Why?

00:28:53.464 --> 00:28:57.463
Guess she's been taking too much time off,
and the trip to DC certainly didn't help.

00:28:57.474 --> 00:28:58.494
Wow.

00:29:00.421 --> 00:29:02.494
Mike, you, uh--
You mind checking us in?

00:29:03.405 --> 00:29:04.495
-I'm gonna go see if she needs anything.
-Sure.

00:29:05.405 --> 00:29:06.488
Martin, you always wanted
to be a pastor.

00:29:06.495 --> 00:29:08.489
Come on, this is what it looks like.

00:29:10.416 --> 00:29:11.428
Okay.

00:29:11.439 --> 00:29:14.438
Taylor, I'm so sorry
to hear about your job.

00:29:14.446 --> 00:29:15.495
Thanks, but I can get another one.

00:29:17.410 --> 00:29:20.426
This one just worked 'cause I could be
with Jackson during the day.

00:29:21.413 --> 00:29:22.426
Okay.

00:29:23.460 --> 00:29:24.480
(SIGHS)

00:29:27.431 --> 00:29:28.490
Is there something else?

00:29:30.451 --> 00:29:32.400
I'm fine.

00:29:32.411 --> 00:29:34.464
Really, you guys don't have
to sit here and hold my hand.

00:29:35.482 --> 00:29:37.431
I'm your pastor, Taylor.

00:29:37.442 --> 00:29:38.465
We're here for you.

00:29:40.499 --> 00:29:42.425
You guys, it's...

00:29:44.416 --> 00:29:46.418
Look, if you don't wanna talk about it,
that's okay.

00:29:47.403 --> 00:29:49.419
But sometimes it's better if you do.

00:29:49.430 --> 00:29:51.466
MARTIN: Everyone is feeling
the stress, I think.

00:29:52.443 --> 00:29:55.480
Shannon said last night she doesn't
want her parents going to jail.

00:29:56.464 --> 00:29:58.447
DAVID: Children shouldn't have
to worry about things like that.

00:29:58.454 --> 00:30:00.467
I know.
She even asked to sleep in our bed.

00:30:00.477 --> 00:30:02.480
I mean, she hasn't done that in years.

00:30:02.488 --> 00:30:04.497
Jackson hasn't slept without me
in over a year.

00:30:11.495 --> 00:30:15.498
My husband left for
an Air Force training mission,

00:30:17.449 --> 00:30:19.448
and that was the last time we saw him.

00:30:20.439 --> 00:30:21.469
Equipment malfunction.

00:30:22.470 --> 00:30:27.403
But I've worked for the government
long enough to read between the lines.

00:30:27.413 --> 00:30:31.404
