What's happening in there?

00:45:45.488 --> 00:45:48.412
They're still running testimony
for the other side.

00:45:48.422 --> 00:45:50.421
They should be finished
in about a half hour,

00:45:51.406 --> 00:45:52.422
and then it's your turn.

00:45:53.406 --> 00:45:55.472
If God is for us,
who can be against us?

00:45:55.479 --> 00:45:58.473
Well, around here,
just about everyone else.

00:46:00.433 --> 00:46:01.493
Maybe I've been in
Washington, DC too long.

00:46:02.400 --> 00:46:04.406
You guys relax.
Come and get you later, okay?

00:46:04.414 --> 00:46:05.413
Thank you.

00:46:10.484 --> 00:46:12.483
What color corsage do I get?

00:46:12.494 --> 00:46:15.411
Depends on what color dress
she's wearing.

00:46:15.418 --> 00:46:16.494
Well, how am I supposed to know that?

00:46:19.415 --> 00:46:21.462
It's kind of like a coral.

00:46:22.452 --> 00:46:24.411
-Coral?
-I got you.

00:46:25.462 --> 00:46:27.409
Everything okay with your grandmother?

00:46:27.416 --> 00:46:28.425
<i>Huh? Oh, yeah.</i>

00:46:28.433 --> 00:46:30.416
(CHUCKLES)
Um, I'm so sorry about that.

00:46:30.426 --> 00:46:32.475
My parents are in Washington.

00:46:32.483 --> 00:46:33.499
As in DC?

00:46:34.410 --> 00:46:35.483
Yeah, they're actually testifying

00:46:35.493 --> 00:46:38.413
at a congressional subcommittee
on homeschooling.

00:46:38.420 --> 00:46:39.419
<i>Wow.</i>

00:46:39.430 --> 00:46:40.497
I bet they must be pumped.

00:46:41.404 --> 00:46:42.447
No, no, no, not really.

00:46:42.454 --> 00:46:44.467
They actually had to go
because a judge here in town

00:46:44.478 --> 00:46:47.468
<i>threatened to fine them
if they didn't send us to public school.</i>

00:46:47.478 --> 00:46:49.411
-Does that look good with coral?
-Yes.

00:46:49.418 --> 00:46:51.462
A judge in Hope Springs?
Which one?

00:46:51.468 --> 00:46:55.428
I don't know, some, uh--
some family judge.

00:46:55.435 --> 00:46:56.495
Hey, I gotta run.
(CHUCKLES)

00:46:57.402 --> 00:46:59.499
<i>-Okay. I'll call you later.</i>
-(LINE BEEPS)

00:47:05.440 --> 00:47:07.416
(MUTTERING)

00:47:11.467 --> 00:47:13.466
Strange place to cram for a test,
Reverend.

00:47:14.437 --> 00:47:16.440
Yeah, this is not really my thing.

00:47:16.451 --> 00:47:19.441
I'm afraid I'm gonna make things worse
for everyone out there.

00:47:20.471 --> 00:47:24.434
Matthew 10:19,
Do not worry about what you will say.

00:47:26.402 --> 00:47:28.438
At that time,
you will be given what to say."

00:47:28.449 --> 00:47:30.432
For it will not be you speaking,

00:47:30.439 --> 00:47:34.469
but the Spirit of your Father
speaking through you."

00:47:34.476 --> 00:47:36.466
There's been a development.

00:47:37.450 --> 00:47:41.416
We have a new chairman, a Robert Benson.

00:47:41.423 --> 00:47:43.443
I'm guessing he's not as friendly
as Abercrombie.

00:47:43.454 --> 00:47:44.453
Hardly.

00:47:44.460 --> 00:47:48.454
The direction out there, the narrative,
is going to change considerably.

00:47:49.444 --> 00:47:51.460
They are going to insist
that religious beliefs

00:47:51.471 --> 00:47:56.424
are anti-rational,
anti-science and antisocial.

00:47:57.435 --> 00:48:01.479
Show them that religious beliefs
are supported through rational thought,

00:48:01.489 --> 00:48:05.409
with a basis on the US law and tradition.

00:48:06.419 --> 00:48:07.472
I think I have a card for that.

00:48:08.453 --> 00:48:12.462
And also, I need you
to make them understand

00:48:12.473 --> 00:48:16.403
that if they insist
on trampling believers' rights,

00:48:16.410 --> 00:48:19.409
well, sir, they are in for a fight.

00:48:20.461 --> 00:48:21.460
You got this.

00:48:27.431 --> 00:48:28.461
SMITH:<i> Mr. Willoughby,</i>

00:48:28.471 --> 00:48:33.448
you have a strong attachment to the idea
of developing a nationalized curriculum,

00:48:33.459 --> 00:48:34.464
do you not?

00:48:34.475 --> 00:48:37.481
Yes, because it's in the best interest
of our children.

00:48:37.492 --> 00:48:39.472
I'm just concerned
that we're working awfully hard here

00:48:39.479 --> 00:48:42.442
to violate one of our own existing laws,

00:48:42.449 --> 00:48:45.490
the Elementary and Secondary
Education Act of 1965,

00:48:45.496 --> 00:48:49.492
which prevents us
from nationalizing any school curriculum.

00:48:50.460 --> 00:48:53.463
I mean, we passed a law
that said we wouldn't do that.

00:48:53.474 --> 00:48:57.497
We've achieved a way
to avoid violating the spirit of that law

00:48:58.408 --> 00:48:59.491
with Common Core.

00:48:59.498 --> 00:49:02.424
We merely propose the guidelines.

00:49:02.498 --> 00:49:04.451
The states adopt the measures
on their own.

00:49:04.462 --> 00:49:07.448
On their own, without any pressure
from the government?

00:49:07.459 --> 00:49:09.428
None whatsoever.

00:49:10.429 --> 00:49:13.482
SMITH: Mr. Willoughby, if you succeed
in gaining approval for your curriculum,

00:49:13.493 --> 00:49:18.402
would parents be able to opt out
or be allowed to opt out of their program?

00:49:18.413 --> 00:49:23.400
I'd encourage the states to require
full participation without exception.

00:49:23.410 --> 00:49:24.493
What gives them the right to do that?

00:49:25.400 --> 00:49:28.480
Well, once we determine
what every child needs to know,

00:49:29.451 --> 00:49:32.467
it becomes imperative
that every child know it.

00:49:32.478 --> 00:49:37.415
After all,
the children belong to all of us.

00:49:37.422 --> 00:49:38.481
SMITH: Interesting perspective.

00:49:38.488 --> 00:49:41.479
There are parents waiting in the wings,

00:49:41.485 --> 00:49:47.482
waiting to testify that their children,
in fact, belong to them...

00:49:49.423 --> 00:49:50.479
and not to all of us.

00:49:52.496 --> 00:49:54.463
But thank you for your candor.

00:49:59.407 --> 00:50:00.440
They're ready for you.

00:50:01.491 --> 00:50:03.421
Okay, come on.

00:50:14.405 --> 00:50:16.454
BENSON: Would the witnesses state
their names for the record?

00:50:16.466 --> 00:50:18.482
MIKE: Yes, sir.
Michael and Rebecca McKinnon.

00:50:19.432 --> 00:50:20.476
Taylor Hays, Your Honor.

00:50:20.486 --> 00:50:25.439
This is not a courtroom, Ms. Hays,
and I most certainly am not a judge.

00:50:25.450 --> 00:50:27.469
Please refer to me as Mr. Chairman.

00:50:27.477 --> 00:50:28.476
And I'm David Hill.

00:50:29.440 --> 00:50:31.434
Reverend David Hill.

00:50:31.440 --> 00:50:33.424
Yes, sir. The preacher.

00:50:34.427 --> 00:50:36.426
We'd like to thank the subcommittee
for having us.

00:50:36.437 --> 00:50:40.437
Um, well, now that who we all are
has been established.

00:50:41.428 --> 00:50:43.475
Mr. Chairman, my husband
and I have our two children

00:50:43.485 --> 00:50:45.478
in the St. Jude homeschooling co-op,

00:50:45.488 --> 00:50:48.491
and they continue to perform better
on standardized testing

00:50:49.402 --> 00:50:51.411
than their public
and private school peers.

00:50:51.422 --> 00:50:54.428
Giving us a good reason to believe
that we're doing something right.

00:50:54.439 --> 00:50:56.419
Well, I should begin by letting you know

00:50:56.426 --> 00:50:59.406
that we've had a series of experts
pass through here,

00:50:59.413 --> 00:51:01.440
all of them assuring us
that we have nothing to fear

00:51:01.447 --> 00:51:03.426
from a standardized education.

00:51:03.437 --> 00:51:06.470
With all due respect,
in this particular case,

00:51:06.477 --> 00:51:10.423
we believe that the experts are wrong.
(CLEARS THROAT)

00:51:10.431 --> 00:51:11.490
Let me give you an example.

00:51:11.498 --> 00:51:14.497
So in our district, they teach
a revisionist version of history,

00:51:15.408 --> 00:51:18.478
which is both progressive
and anti-faith in equal measure.

00:51:18.488 --> 00:51:21.458
And so if our children are forced
onto its Common Core track,

00:51:21.465 --> 00:51:24.425
they will never learn
about the faith-based underpinnings

00:51:24.432 --> 00:51:26.481
of the US Constitution
or its Bill of Rights.

00:51:26.493 --> 00:51:28.479
They'll never hear
about George Washington's plea

00:51:28.489 --> 00:51:31.483
for the blessing of almighty God
at his inauguration.

00:51:31.493 --> 00:51:34.423
MIKE: They're not taught anything
that reflects positively

00:51:34.430 --> 00:51:36.413
on America's Christian heritage,

00:51:36.423 --> 00:51:40.400
despite the fact that America's history
and its faith traditions

00:51:40.411 --> 00:51:41.440
are so deeply intertwined.

00:51:41.447 --> 00:51:45.443
Well, that is not what our experts
have testified to here today.

00:51:45.451 --> 00:51:46.460
What about Thanksgiving?

00:51:47.451 --> 00:51:48.484
-Excuse me?
-DAVID: Thanksgiving.

00:51:48.495 --> 00:51:51.464
You know, pilgrims, turkeys,
Native Americans.

00:51:51.475 --> 00:51:54.412
-I'm familiar with the holiday.
-DAVID: Well, sure you are.

00:51:54.419 --> 00:51:56.478
From kindergarten onward,
every child learns about it.

00:51:56.486 --> 00:51:58.479
But what do they learn?

00:51:58.486 --> 00:52:02.466
This is the NEA's own statement
regarding Thanksgiving.

00:52:03.466 --> 00:52:07.410
The National Education Association
believes that Thanksgiving

00:52:07.417 --> 00:52:10.460
is the recognition of unity
and the rich American diversity

00:52:10.467 --> 00:52:12.493
that was embodied
in the settlement of America."

00:52:13.400 --> 00:52:14.484
Well, that sounds completely reasonable.

00:52:14.494 --> 00:52:18.450
Well, that would've come as a big surprise
to the pilgrims that were actually there.

00:52:19.428 --> 00:52:21.480
They came together
to thank God for the bountiful harvest.

00:52:22.448 --> 00:52:26.471
Now, the Native Americans
were fellow guests. Yes, absolutely.

00:52:26.482 --> 00:52:29.405
But God was the reason for the feast.

00:52:29.415 --> 00:52:31.482
And to indicate that the purpose
of the first Thanksgiving

00:52:31.489 --> 00:52:35.469
was primarily a multicultural event
is a fabrication.

00:52:35.479 --> 00:52:38.416
And if we don't teach
the Common Core myth,

00:52:38.423 --> 00:52:40.466
then Social Services and a--

00:52:41.467 --> 00:52:43.429
a judge in Hope Springs

00:52:43.437 --> 00:52:46.450
has decided that we risk
going to jail for contempt.

00:52:48.401 --> 00:52:49.463
It's your babysitter.
She said it's urgent.

00:52:49.471 --> 00:52:50.470
Thank you.

00:52:50.481 --> 00:52:52.404
Hello, Meredith?

00:52:52.414 --> 00:52:55.455
Taylor, Jackson's not hurt.

00:52:55.465 --> 00:52:58.417
It's just he's been crying all day.

00:52:58.425 --> 00:53:02.448
<i>And now he's refusing to eat.
I thought maybe you could talk to him.</i>

00:53:02.455 --> 00:53:04.475
Of course. Can you put him
on the phone, please?

00:53:06.432 --> 00:53:08.409
It's your mama, Jackson.

00:53:10.460 --> 00:53:12.400
<i>Mommy?</i>

00:53:12.406 --> 00:53:15.416
Hi, honey. Are you having a bad day?

00:53:16.420 --> 00:53:18.419
Are you coming back?

00:53:18.427 --> 00:53:20.493
<i>Yes, sweetheart. Mommy always comes back.</i>

00:53:22.427 --> 00:53:24.424
I'll be home as soon as I can.

00:53:24.434 --> 00:53:27.404
Hey, did you know
that this is where the president lives?

00:53:27.411 --> 00:53:29.424
<i>Come back. Don't go to heaven.</i>

00:53:29.435 --> 00:53:30.494
<i>Stay with me.</i>

00:53:33.435 --> 00:53:35.418
Mommy always comes back.

00:53:36.402 --> 00:53:38.405
<i>You'll feel better if you eat your lunch.</i>

00:53:38.412 --> 00:53:40.402
<i>Please eat something, honey.</i>

00:53:42.476 --> 00:53:43.489
Love you, sweetheart.

00:53:43.496 --> 00:53:46.452
MEREDITH:<i> Jackson,
let's go get something to eat, okay?</i>

00:53:47.480 --> 00:53:48.479
(LINE BEEPS)

00:53:53.461 --> 00:53:54.487
2:00 p.m.?

00:53:58.461 --> 00:54:00.444
Where is Ayisha Moradi?

00:54:00.455 --> 00:54:03.414
-Relation to the patient?
-I'm her father.

00:54:05.478 --> 00:54:06.477
(PHONE HOOK CLICKS)

00:54:06.489 --> 00:54:08.411
She'll be in 302.

00:54:15.456 --> 00:54:16.482
You know that, don't you?

00:54:17.460 --> 00:54:18.459
That I love you?

00:54:19.480 --> 00:54:21.416
AYISHA:<i> Yes, Baba.</i>

00:54:23.417 --> 00:54:24.433
Ayisha!

00:54:27.484 --> 00:54:30.478
<i>He's the one God who has not begotten.</i>

00:54:31.478 --> 00:54:33.407
I command you to say it.

00:54:33.498 --> 00:54:34.497
Now!

00:54:38.465 --> 00:54:40.498
AYISHA: Baba! No, Baba!

00:54:49.496 --> 00:54:52.443
No, no!

00:55:18.422 --> 00:55:19.456
I'm sorry.

00:55:25.480 --> 00:55:29.479
BENSON: My concern is that our children
will not live up to their full potential

00:55:29.487 --> 00:55:32.413
{\an8}by being subject
to a faith-based education

00:55:32.420 --> 00:55:34.497
{\an8}which is anti-rational and anti-science.

00:55:38.418 --> 00:55:39.441
May I say something?

00:55:40.488 --> 00:55:42.454
That's why you're here, Ms. Hays.

00:55:43.488 --> 00:55:46.441
Belief in the Bible isn't anti-science.

00:55:47.442 --> 00:55:49.405
What is your occupation?

00:55:51.406 --> 00:55:54.432
It says here you're an assistant manager
in a restaurant.

00:55:54.439 --> 00:55:56.405
Recently unemployed.

00:55:58.403 --> 00:55:59.426
What else do your notes say?

00:55:59.436 --> 00:56:02.436
Well, there doesn't really appear
to be too much here.

00:56:02.443 --> 00:56:04.410
TAYLOR:
Let me fill in the blanks for you.

00:56:05.487 --> 00:56:07.407
I'm a widow.

00:56:08.404 --> 00:56:09.470
After my husband passed away,

00:56:09.477 --> 00:56:12.474
I took a less demanding job
to spend more time with our son.

00:56:12.484 --> 00:56:14.454
You have my condolences.

00:56:14.461 --> 00:56:16.451
But before he died,

00:56:16.458 --> 00:56:20.452
I completed an advanced degree
in aerospace engineering

00:56:20.459 --> 00:56:23.418
and worked as a systems engineer
in Houston

00:56:23.425 --> 00:56:26.462
at the National Aeronautics
and Space Administration.

00:56:26.472 --> 00:56:28.402
NASA.

00:56:28.459 --> 00:56:33.412
NASA has a long history
with men and women of faith.

00:56:34.407 --> 00:56:36.406
Do you know what the first
food and beverage

00:56:36.413 --> 00:56:38.410
ever consumed on the surface
of the moon was?

00:56:38.420 --> 00:56:41.423
I have no idea. Tang, I suppose.

00:56:41.431 --> 00:56:42.430
(CHUCKLES)

00:56:43.421 --> 00:56:44.480
Consecrated bread and wine.

00:56:45.444 --> 00:56:48.481
It happened when astronaut Buzz Aldrin
took Holy Communion

00:56:48.491 --> 00:56:52.437
just after setting down the lunar module
in the Sea of Tranquility.

00:56:52.445 --> 00:56:56.432
<i>You see, Aldrin was an elder
at Webster Presbyterian Church,</i>

00:56:56.442 --> 00:56:59.448
<i>and he got special permission
to take the bread and wine with him</i>

00:56:59.459 --> 00:57:01.449
and give himself communion.

00:57:01.459 --> 00:57:03.458
A few months earlier on Christmas Eve,

00:57:03.466 --> 00:57:06.443
<i>the crew of Apollo 8
read from the Book of Genesis</i>

00:57:06.450 --> 00:57:07.476
<i>while they orbited the moon.</i>

00:57:07.483 --> 00:57:10.496
An Israeli astronaut, Ilan Ramon,
recited the Jewish Shabbat kiddush,

00:57:11.407 --> 00:57:13.433
and Russian cosmonaut, Sergey Ryzhikov--

00:57:13.444 --> 00:57:14.493
What is your point, Ms. Hays?

00:57:15.401 --> 00:57:17.431
There's a common misconception
of homeschool parents,

00:57:17.441 --> 00:57:20.481
particularly those of faith,
that we're some kind of flat-earthers.

00:57:21.461 --> 00:57:25.431
My seven-year-old
knows that the Earth is round

00:57:25.442 --> 00:57:29.408
and that the sunrise is an illusion
caused by the Earth's rotation.

00:57:29.415 --> 00:57:31.465
And when tested in physics or chemistry

00:57:31.476 --> 00:57:34.419
about the rate of acceleration
of a falling object

00:57:34.429 --> 00:57:38.475
or the atomic mass of cesium,
acceptable answers do not include, "Jesus"

00:57:38.483 --> 00:57:40.466
or, "Whatever God wants it to be."

00:57:41.671 --> 00:57:42.732
And lastly,

00:57:44.414 --> 00:57:48.413
my husband was a United States
Air Force pilot

00:57:48.481 --> 00:57:52.444
who fought for our freedoms
and died in service to this country.

00:57:53.428 --> 00:57:58.411
So if it's all the same to you,
I would prefer you call me Mrs. Hays

00:57:58.418 --> 00:58:02.428
out of respect of my marriage
and to my husband's memory.

00:58:02.435 --> 00:58:03.469
(ATTENDEES MURMURING)

00:58:09.449 --> 00:58:12.440
(PANEL MURMURING)

00:58:17.470 --> 00:58:20.450
Your nation thanks your husband
for his service

00:58:20.457 --> 00:58:23.413
and you and your family
for your sacrifice.

00:58:23.421 --> 00:58:25.484
I'm afraid that's all the time
we have here today.

00:58:26.454 --> 00:58:28.498
This hearing is now adjourned
till tomorrow morning.

00:58:32.445 --> 00:58:34.401
(DOOR CLOSES)

00:58:34.409 --> 00:58:35.499
I don't know what
you're talking about.

00:58:36.452 --> 00:58:37.468
No.

00:58:37.476 --> 00:58:38.492
No, I just got home.

00:58:41.409 --> 00:58:42.425
Hold on.

00:58:43.493 --> 00:58:48.433
<i>The parents of St. Jude co-op are only
asking Social Services and Judge Neely</i>

00:58:48.440 --> 00:58:51.449
<i>to allow us to supervise
the education of our children</i>

00:58:51.457 --> 00:58:53.420
<i>as best as we know how.</i>

00:58:53.427 --> 00:58:55.471
<i>And they continue to perform higher
on standardized tests</i>

00:58:55.477 --> 00:58:57.450
<i>than their public
and private school peers.</i>

00:58:57.458 --> 00:58:58.457
I'll call you back.

00:58:58.468 --> 00:59:00.467
<i>-Giving us a good reason to believe...</i>
-Mom?

00:59:00.475 --> 00:59:02.471
<i>...we're doing something right.</i>

00:59:02.485 --> 00:59:06.461
She has no bone fractures,
no internal injuries or bleeding.

00:59:07.442 --> 00:59:09.435
Then why won't she wake up?

00:59:10.459 --> 00:59:12.452
Head trauma.

00:59:12.459 --> 00:59:15.442
But she's young and in good health.

00:59:16.403 --> 00:59:18.490
I'm hopeful she'll recover
without any serious repercussions.

00:59:18.496 --> 00:59:20.412
Hopeful?

00:59:23.423 --> 00:59:27.407
Are you a religious man, Mr. Moradi?

00:59:27.414 --> 00:59:28.440
Yes, of course.

00:59:28.447 --> 00:59:29.491
Why do you ask?

00:59:30.471 --> 00:59:33.454
I thought you might be comforted
in prayer.

00:59:33.461 --> 00:59:34.460
Prayer?

00:59:36.415 --> 00:59:37.441
It can't hurt.

00:59:54.430 --> 00:59:55.466
May I be excused?

00:59:57.444 --> 00:59:59.480
-You have something to say, say it.
-Okay.

01:00:00.461 --> 01:00:02.480
It's kind of weird to find out
that your mom is the one

01:00:02.491 --> 01:00:04.467
who's sending your friend's parents
to jail.

01:00:04.478 --> 01:00:06.480
You know I don't send people to jail.

01:00:06.491 --> 01:00:10.425
They put themselves in jail
by refusing to follow the law.

01:00:10.431 --> 01:00:12.418
And since when do you
have homeschooled friends?

01:00:12.428 --> 01:00:14.465
-Since when is homeschooling illegal?
-Watch your tone.

01:00:18.469 --> 01:00:22.415
The state has set universal standards
for education.

01:00:22.426 --> 01:00:25.436
Homeschoolers can't pick and choose
the ones that they wanna follow.

01:00:25.446 --> 01:00:27.499
But don't they have to take the same tests
that we do?

01:00:28.410 --> 01:00:30.493
Who cares what road they take
if we all end up in the same place?

01:00:31.400 --> 01:00:32.410
That's just the point.

01:00:32.417 --> 01:00:33.487
We don't end up in the same place,

01:00:33.497 --> 01:00:36.467
because the roads that they take
are paved with privilege.

01:00:36.477 --> 01:00:39.444
Why does every conversation
have to go back to--

01:00:39.451 --> 01:00:43.464
Homeschooling is separatist,
elitist and racist, Kayla.

01:00:43.471 --> 01:00:47.438
And I didn't raise you
to challenge me this way in my own home.

01:00:49.455 --> 01:00:51.461
Actually, you kind of did.

01:00:51.469 --> 01:00:53.452
TAYLOR:<i> So where did Martin run off to?</i>

01:00:54.429 --> 01:00:57.432
He's off on a fact-finding mission
with some tourists that he met.

01:00:57.440 --> 01:01:00.416
TAYLOR: Oh, bless his heart.
He's so happy to be here.

01:01:00.423 --> 01:01:01.422
(SIGHS)

01:01:01.433 --> 01:01:03.463
I was too, but I'm not so sure now.

01:01:03.470 --> 01:01:05.497
I just have no idea
how we're doing in there.

01:01:06.404 --> 01:01:07.453
Have we heard anything
from Congressman Smith?

01:01:07.464 --> 01:01:08.480
Not yet.

01:01:09.441 --> 01:01:10.474
We should call the kids.

01:01:10.484 --> 01:01:12.447
All right, excuse us.

01:01:12.454 --> 01:01:14.407
-Let's go in the back.
-Okay.

01:01:15.421 --> 01:01:16.470
-(PHONE CHIMES)
-Ah.

01:01:17.448 --> 01:01:18.435
Food's here.

01:01:18.442 --> 01:01:20.408
-I'm gonna run down and get it.
-Thanks.

01:01:21.405 --> 01:01:25.499
Hey, maybe it'll help to know
that we're here for you.

01:01:28.403 --> 01:01:29.486
You have a family in St. Jude's.

01:01:39.457 --> 01:01:43.470
(DENISE CHUCKLES) Where did Smith
dig up a dead soldier's wife?

01:01:44.434 --> 01:01:46.407
Benson needs to vet
the witness list better.

01:01:46.471 --> 01:01:50.444
And anyone buying the holy-roller story
that she used to work at NASA?

01:01:50.455 --> 01:01:52.488
Hey, someone has to empty out
the garbage cans, am I right?

01:01:52.495 --> 01:01:56.408
How much longer
do we have to suffer through this?

01:01:56.419 --> 01:01:57.495
I got better places to be.

01:02:00.436 --> 01:02:02.435
-Uh, no, you can keep it.
-Thank you.

01:02:09.400 --> 01:02:11.473
DENISE: Reverend Hill,
how do you answer the comment

01:02:11.480 --> 01:02:16.464
by former US commission on civil rights,
Chairman Martin Castro, and here I quote,

01:02:16.474 --> 01:02:19.447
The phrases
religious liberty and religious freedom

01:02:19.458 --> 01:02:22.427
will stand for nothing except hypocrisy,

01:02:22.438 --> 01:02:26.455
as long as they remain code words
for discrimination, intolerance, racism,

01:02:26.462 --> 01:02:30.475
sexism, homophobia, Islamophobia
or any form of intolerance"?

01:02:30.482 --> 01:02:34.445
I think it says more about the bias
of the former civil rights chairman

01:02:34.456 --> 01:02:37.412
than it does about
the supposed biases of believers.

01:02:37.423 --> 01:02:42.410
But surely you recognize how offensively
patriarchal and sexist the Bible is.

01:02:42.417 --> 01:02:43.473
Is that a legitimate question,

01:02:43.480 --> 01:02:45.474
or is that just your chance
at a sound bite?

01:02:45.480 --> 01:02:47.417
(ATTENDEES CHUCKLING)

01:02:47.427 --> 01:02:48.426
-(GAVEL BANGS)
-Quiet.

01:02:48.434 --> 01:02:49.457
Excuse me?

01:02:50.434 --> 01:02:51.447
I--

01:02:51.458 --> 01:02:53.417
Considering the time when it was written,

01:02:53.428 --> 01:02:56.468
the Bible is one of the most
pro-feminist documents in history.

01:02:56.478 --> 01:02:59.484
In an era where women were treated
as property to be bought and sold...

01:02:59.495 --> 01:03:03.401
Paul ordered women to cover up their hair,

01:03:03.412 --> 01:03:04.465
to wear a veil in the assembly.

01:03:05.419 --> 01:03:07.425
Do you think I need
to wear a veil for you?

01:03:07.433 --> 01:03:09.469
Single women in the Roman Empire

01:03:09.479 --> 01:03:14.499
were required by law to unveil their hair
for the visual pleasure of men.

01:03:15.463 --> 01:03:19.420
It would be like today if we forced
a young woman to dress immodestly

01:03:19.430 --> 01:03:21.414
and it was totally exploitative.

01:03:21.471 --> 01:03:24.477
To get around that,
you either had to be married or widowed.

01:03:24.484 --> 01:03:29.414
So when Paul told women
to wear a veil in the assembly,

01:03:29.421 --> 01:03:31.427
he was adding to the dignity of women,

01:03:32.405 --> 01:03:35.432
basically saying, "You are every bit
as good as a married woman or a widow

01:03:35.439 --> 01:03:39.462
and you don't have to put yourself
on display, at least not in here."

01:03:41.403 --> 01:03:42.486
(FOOTSTEPS)

01:03:45.483 --> 01:03:46.482
Mom?

01:03:48.407 --> 01:03:49.456
I'd like to make an argument.

01:03:50.453 --> 01:03:51.497
I'm already late.

01:03:52.404 --> 01:03:53.413
It's important.

01:03:53.420 --> 01:03:54.483
(SIGHS) Five minutes.

01:03:56.467 --> 01:03:58.417
In the matter of

01:03:58.424 --> 01:04:00.480
<i>The State v. the St. Jude's
Homeschooling Cooperative--</i>

01:04:00.488 --> 01:04:02.421
That case has been decided.

01:04:02.431 --> 01:04:04.431
Is the court's decision
not subject to appeal?

01:04:04.438 --> 01:04:07.455
-Grounds?
-New evidence, conflicting evidence.

01:04:07.465 --> 01:04:10.425
-Four minutes.
-Point of clarification.

01:04:10.435 --> 01:04:12.419
How is homeschooling socially selfish

01:04:12.426 --> 01:04:14.438
and misaligned
with liberal progressive values?

01:04:14.449 --> 01:04:17.455
Because it ignores
the needs of the community at large.

01:04:17.466 --> 01:04:19.486
We're divided enough as it is, Kayla.

01:04:19.493 --> 01:04:21.433
We shouldn't be teaching our children

01:04:21.440 --> 01:04:24.486
to be suspicious of public institutions
and civic obligations.

01:04:24.494 --> 01:04:28.420
What if Christian homeschoolers
are more likely to donate to charities

01:04:28.427 --> 01:04:30.440
or be first in line
to volunteer in Third World countries?

01:04:30.451 --> 01:04:32.403
There's no evidence of that.

01:04:32.411 --> 01:04:33.494
-Mom, they're literally Christians.
-(SIGHS)

01:04:34.404 --> 01:04:36.491
Who do you think does most
of the donating and volunteering?

01:04:37.401 --> 01:04:39.407
You've always told me that
there's value in dissent

01:04:39.418 --> 01:04:40.491
and challenging prevailing norms.

01:04:41.402 --> 01:04:43.411
Isn't that the foundation
for liberal activism?

01:04:43.422 --> 01:04:45.435
What about institutional diversity?

01:04:45.442 --> 01:04:46.472
Look, all I'm saying is,

01:04:46.479 --> 01:04:50.406
shouldn't there be options for education,
choices for the individual,

01:04:50.413 --> 01:04:53.453
instead of lumping everyone together
in a single one-size-fits-all model?

01:04:53.460 --> 01:04:55.412
How is that diversity?

01:04:55.423 --> 01:04:59.436
The public school system
is there for us as a society.

01:04:59.444 --> 01:05:01.420
The people are not there for it.

01:05:01.427 --> 01:05:05.447
As soon as it stops working for the kids,
parents are obligated to leave.

01:05:11.432 --> 01:05:12.475
MIKE:<i> The parents
of the homeschooling co-op</i>

01:05:12.482 --> 01:05:14.495
take seriously
our duty to instruct our children,

01:05:15.489 --> 01:05:18.488
to teach them, to educate them,
to decide what is best for them.

01:05:18.496 --> 01:05:21.465
It's a natural extension of our beliefs.

01:05:21.476 --> 01:05:24.466
Beliefs that I consider
to be divisive and intolerant.

01:05:24.476 --> 01:05:28.449
Only because you label intolerant
anyone who you don't agree with,

01:05:28.460 --> 01:05:31.443
and you label divisive
as anyone who doesn't agree with you.

01:05:32.400 --> 01:05:35.413
The gospels describe Jesus
as teaching his followers

01:05:35.424 --> 01:05:39.427
to forgive each other,
to love their enemies,

01:05:39.434 --> 01:05:41.414
show generosity to those in need

01:05:41.425 --> 01:05:43.494
and embrace those
outside their ethnic circles.

01:05:44.401 --> 01:05:45.464
Would you call that divisive?

01:05:45.475 --> 01:05:48.431
Christ commanded his followers
to advance his message

01:05:48.442 --> 01:05:52.429
with the irresistible force of love
and the power of truth.

01:05:52.499 --> 01:05:54.458
Would you call that intolerant?

01:05:54.466 --> 01:05:57.446
No one has a monopoly on the truth,
Mr. Hill. Not even you.

01:05:57.453 --> 01:06:01.459
No. But if God exists,
then he has the monopoly on it

01:06:01.467 --> 01:06:04.483
and we hold that he does exist
and has spoken.

01:06:04.494 --> 01:06:06.430
Your truth, sir, not mine.

01:06:06.437 --> 01:06:08.443
DAVID: Except that's not the way
that truth works.

01:06:08.451 --> 01:06:11.427
Truth is truth
for everyone and everywhere.

01:06:11.481 --> 01:06:16.494
Even if over time, it loses its popularity
or becomes politically incorrect.

01:06:17.462 --> 01:06:20.438
That's what the parents
of these children understand.

01:06:20.448 --> 01:06:24.448
That in a society where
suddenly everything is relative,

01:06:24.456 --> 01:06:29.446
truth is absolute,
a transcendent thing not of this world.

01:06:29.453 --> 01:06:32.436
Something that they have
no power to change.

01:06:32.446 --> 01:06:36.446
America was founded on these principles,
and if we just throw them away--

01:06:36.453 --> 01:06:37.466
I think we're done here.

01:06:37.474 --> 01:06:40.403
I would like to thank the witnesses
for their input.

01:06:40.414 --> 01:06:41.423
They're free to go.

01:06:41.434 --> 01:06:43.471
This hearing is now adjourned
for one hour.

01:06:43.481 --> 01:06:46.414
After which,
we will vote on this issue.

01:06:49.418 --> 01:06:50.417
DAVID: Mr. Chairman.

01:06:50.485 --> 01:06:53.468
Mr. Chairman, you haven't ruled
on our situation.

01:06:53.475 --> 01:06:57.442
I'm sorry, sir, that you have
misunderstood the purpose of this hearing.

01:06:57.452 --> 01:06:58.451
Thank you.

01:07:00.402 --> 01:07:02.443
Wait, what does he mean
"The purpose of this hearing"?

01:07:02.453 --> 01:07:05.416
I'm not sure.
I mean, is any of this going to matter?

01:07:05.423 --> 01:07:06.442
It has to.

01:07:06.453 --> 01:07:08.493
I mean, even when it turns out
we're still under a court order

01:07:09.403 --> 01:07:11.453
and facing all kinds of fines
when we get home?

01:07:18.424 --> 01:07:19.454
Are you sure?

01:07:20.488 --> 01:07:21.487
Yeah.

01:07:23.401 --> 01:07:24.400
I see.

01:07:26.435 --> 01:07:27.434
Okay.

01:07:28.429 --> 01:07:29.455
Have a safe flight.

01:07:33.492 --> 01:07:35.452
Is Mommy coming home?

01:07:36.413 --> 01:07:37.459
Mommy's coming home.

01:07:46.410 --> 01:07:47.430
(SIGHS)

01:07:47.491 --> 01:07:49.410
{\an8}(PHONE DINGS)

01:07:53.491 --> 01:07:55.447
BENSON: I'm impressed, Mr. Hill.

01:07:57.415 --> 01:07:59.478
You really should have had yourself
a career in politics.

01:07:59.488 --> 01:08:00.487
Thanks.

01:08:01.465 --> 01:08:02.492
I'll pass.

01:08:02.499 --> 01:08:05.415
Do you really think anything
you said in there

01:08:05.426 --> 01:08:07.459
is gonna have any effect on what we do?

01:08:08.479 --> 01:08:12.496
You see, we do these things
because we're supposed to,

01:08:13.406 --> 01:08:14.483
because supposedly somebody's watching.

01:08:15.460 --> 01:08:20.409
But other than a few C-SPAN junkies,
is anybody really paying attention?

01:08:20.497 --> 01:08:22.423
Don't you get it?

01:08:22.497 --> 01:08:25.494
We've already decided
what we're gonna do.

01:08:26.401 --> 01:08:27.450
(SIGHS)

01:08:27.461 --> 01:08:30.478
Or you wouldn't be having these hearings
in the first place.

01:08:30.485 --> 01:08:32.451
Look, I understand your position.

01:08:32.462 --> 01:08:36.414
You feel that you're making
a last-ditch stand for your faith,

01:08:36.425 --> 01:08:39.431
and you've chosen this
as a hill that you're willing to die on.

01:08:39.442 --> 01:08:42.466
Our whole faith started because one man
chose a hill he was willing to die on.

01:08:42.476 --> 01:08:47.470
Yes, but that was a long time ago
and now nobody really cares.

01:08:47.480 --> 01:08:51.450
Let's face it, your God, your book,
they're in the way.

01:08:51.460 --> 01:08:53.466
They're in the way of moral relativism.

01:08:54.461 --> 01:08:57.410
They're in the way
of calling good evil and evil good.

01:08:57.417 --> 01:08:59.480
What did you plan to accomplish here today?

01:09:01.421 --> 01:09:05.411
To defend the rights of parents
to educate their children as they see fit.

01:09:05.418 --> 01:09:06.465
And to make Congress promise

01:09:06.472 --> 01:09:08.495
that they will never threaten
those rights again.

01:09:09.402 --> 01:09:10.495
-Yes.
-Sir, that is not gonna happen.

01:09:11.462 --> 01:09:13.461
In a few minutes,
we're gonna go back in there,

01:09:13.469 --> 01:09:15.418
we're gonna take a quick straw vote,

01:09:15.429 --> 01:09:18.463
which is gonna find in favor
of the experts' recommendations.

01:09:18.470 --> 01:09:20.403
Experts.

01:09:20.413 --> 01:09:22.457
And then we're gonna push this through
just like we planned.

01:09:23.497 --> 01:09:25.473
-Just like that?
-Just like that.

01:09:29.464 --> 01:09:33.417
I'd be careful about going to war
against God's church.

01:09:33.424 --> 01:09:36.448
Scripture promises the gates of hell
will not prevail against it.

01:09:36.455 --> 01:09:38.468
This is not hell, Mr. Hill.

01:09:38.475 --> 01:09:39.474
This is Washington.

01:09:39.485 --> 01:09:41.405
Close enough.

01:09:42.439 --> 01:09:45.448
For 2,000 years,
men have tried to get rid of Christianity.

01:09:46.456 --> 01:09:51.409
Diocletian, Napoleon, Stalin, Mao Zedong.

01:09:52.486 --> 01:09:55.439
What makes you think that you
can accomplish what they couldn't?

01:09:56.440 --> 01:09:58.484
They didn't have an 83% approval rating.

01:10:08.401 --> 01:10:09.421
BENSON: Daryl.

01:10:10.495 --> 01:10:13.461
I really thought the Lord
would intervene on our behalf.

01:10:13.472 --> 01:10:18.418
Before you say anything else,
I wanna show you all something.

01:10:19.472 --> 01:10:20.485
Follow me.

01:10:27.460 --> 01:10:29.403
You want to talk?

01:10:30.473 --> 01:10:32.403
Let's talk!

01:10:35.457 --> 01:10:36.477
Huh?

01:10:37.471 --> 01:10:39.414
Did you say something?

01:10:40.461 --> 01:10:42.431
I didn't hear you.

01:10:44.415 --> 01:10:48.471
They say you're a man.
Then come down and face me like one.

01:10:50.482 --> 01:10:52.462
You're more than a man, no?

01:10:54.493 --> 01:10:56.412
You see all.

01:10:57.423 --> 01:10:58.439
You know all.

01:10:59.406 --> 01:11:04.430
Then tell me, Son of God,
why did you take Ayisha from me?

01:11:04.440 --> 01:11:05.499
She's my daughter.

01:11:07.497 --> 01:11:09.456
Are you punishing her?

01:11:12.424 --> 01:11:13.490
Did she displease you?

01:11:18.498 --> 01:11:22.465
Or are you punishing me?

01:11:35.400 --> 01:11:36.416
I beg of you...

01:11:38.420 --> 01:11:42.466
if you must have blood, take mine instead.

01:11:43.444 --> 01:11:46.414
(WHIMPERING) Let Ayisha live.

01:11:47.438 --> 01:11:49.418
I'll do anything.

01:11:51.432 --> 01:11:52.448
Anything.

01:12:00.406 --> 01:12:01.449
(GROANS)

01:12:03.429 --> 01:12:04.489
(FLOORBOARD CREAKS)

01:12:33.489 --> 01:12:38.433
Everybody knows her big sister,
Lady Liberty,

01:12:38.440 --> 01:12:40.406
who stands in New York Harbor.

01:12:41.460 --> 01:12:42.483
But this one?

01:12:44.450 --> 01:12:45.456
She's my girl.

01:12:46.460 --> 01:12:48.427
She's a replica.

01:12:48.437 --> 01:12:49.460
Do you know her story?

01:12:52.428 --> 01:12:55.427
The bronze was cast in 1861
outside of Washington.

01:12:55.438 --> 01:12:57.428
Her name is Freedom.

01:12:58.478 --> 01:13:01.412
And in one of those ironies
that God seems to delight in,

01:13:01.422 --> 01:13:05.459
Philip Reid, the foundry foreman
in charge of casting her, was a slave.

01:13:05.469 --> 01:13:08.435
A gifted artisan,
but a slave nonetheless.

01:13:09.406 --> 01:13:12.479
But by the time the Capitol dome
was ready to receive her in 1863,

01:13:12.490 --> 01:13:15.453
the Emancipation Proclamation
was in full effect.

01:13:16.480 --> 01:13:21.457
Meaning that Philip Reid
most likely stood outside of this building

01:13:21.464 --> 01:13:24.437
and watched her go aloft as a free man.

01:13:26.414 --> 01:13:29.424
And all the hands
that strained at the hoisting ropes

01:13:29.431 --> 01:13:31.431
all belonged to former slaves.

01:13:34.412 --> 01:13:35.445
In my mind,

01:13:37.409 --> 01:13:40.475
any country that can do that
is worth fighting for.

01:13:41.473 --> 01:13:45.425
So that is exactly what we need to do...
keep fighting.

01:13:47.400 --> 01:13:50.493
You at home and me right here.

01:13:54.497 --> 01:13:56.477
They're gonna be taking the vote soon.

01:13:57.441 --> 01:14:00.464
Um, I need to get back in
and prepare my closing statements.

01:14:00.474 --> 01:14:03.408
They only gave me five minutes,
but I'll take it.

01:14:03.475 --> 01:14:04.498
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

01:14:07.499 --> 01:14:09.401
My pleasure.

01:14:13.469 --> 01:14:15.418
You all did wonderful.

01:14:17.403 --> 01:14:18.402
Thanks, Martin.

01:14:19.446 --> 01:14:22.409
Kind of felt
like the fight was rigged though.

01:14:22.417 --> 01:14:25.476
Founding Fathers didn't account
for the likes of Chairman Benson.

01:14:26.477 --> 01:14:30.417
Governor Morris was a Founding Father,
and he wrote,

01:14:30.427 --> 01:14:33.487
"Religion is the only solid basis
of good morals.

01:14:33.498 --> 01:14:37.444
"Therefore, education should teach
the precepts of religion

01:14:37.451 --> 01:14:39.495
"and the duties of man towards God."

01:14:40.402 --> 01:14:41.488
DAVID: Those days are past.

01:14:41.499 --> 01:14:44.445
Mr. Morris didn't stand the test of time.

01:14:45.402 --> 01:14:46.401
But he did.

01:14:46.412 --> 01:14:50.403
Maybe this other thing he wrote
will be more familiar to you...

01:14:50.499 --> 01:14:55.440
"We the people of the United States,
in order to form a more perfect union--"

01:14:55.450 --> 01:14:57.430
"Establish justice."

01:14:57.437 --> 01:14:59.406
"Ensure domestic tranquility."

01:14:59.417 --> 01:15:02.497
"Provide for the common defense
and promote general welfare."

01:15:04.401 --> 01:15:05.498
"And secure the blessings of liberty."

01:15:06.404 --> 01:15:07.407
Liberty.

01:15:07.418 --> 01:15:08.420
Liberty.

01:15:08.431 --> 01:15:11.421
"Do ordain and establish
this Constitution."

01:15:11.431 --> 01:15:13.441
"For the United States of America."

01:15:18.409 --> 01:15:20.485
I'm sorry. I saw you all inside.

01:15:20.492 --> 01:15:23.466
-I--
-ATTENDEE: We're the other 75%.

01:15:24.426 --> 01:15:25.475
Three-quarters of parents who homeschool

01:15:25.486 --> 01:15:28.406
for other than
primarily religious reasons.

01:15:28.417 --> 01:15:30.403
Three-quarters? I mean, I thought that--

01:15:30.410 --> 01:15:31.423
That's what most people think,

01:15:31.433 --> 01:15:34.436
that at all homeschoolers
are conservative Christians.

01:15:34.444 --> 01:15:35.443
That's not true.

01:15:36.461 --> 01:15:38.458
Robert Williams from NBHE.

01:15:38.468 --> 01:15:39.473
Nice to meet you.

01:15:39.484 --> 01:15:42.411
We homeschool
because most of the schools in my area

01:15:42.421 --> 01:15:44.427
are chronically underfunded.

01:15:44.438 --> 01:15:46.468
(CHUCKLES) Not to mention
institutionalized racism.

01:15:46.475 --> 01:15:48.495
-Mm-hmm.
-My son has special needs.

01:15:49.405 --> 01:15:51.439
Public schools just aren't equipped.

01:15:51.446 --> 01:15:53.422
Medical freedom.

01:15:53.429 --> 01:15:56.492
I want to be able to choose
which immunizations my children receive.

01:15:57.403 --> 01:16:00.419
Bullying, violence, school shootings.

01:16:00.426 --> 01:16:01.479
There are many reasons.

01:16:01.490 --> 01:16:03.413
Low student-to-teacher ratio.

01:16:03.480 --> 01:16:06.486
Parents can choose the pace
and approach of the classroom.

01:16:06.494 --> 01:16:10.481
Yeah, we have time for community service,
volunteering and entrepreneurship.

01:16:10.491 --> 01:16:13.493
Not to mention the arts, outdoor play
and real experiments.

01:16:14.404 --> 01:16:16.421
-(ALL CHUCKLE)
-First things public schools cut

01:16:16.428 --> 01:16:17.430
to save money.

01:16:17.441 --> 01:16:20.404
-Yeah.
-Our reasons might be different,

01:16:20.412 --> 01:16:21.461
but we all want the same thing.

01:16:21.472 --> 01:16:25.475
As long as government overreach
goes unchecked, liberty is threatened.

01:16:26.459 --> 01:16:27.458
All of ours.

01:16:27.466 --> 01:16:28.482
We can't stop.

01:16:28.493 --> 01:16:30.459
We're stronger together.

01:16:30.466 --> 01:16:32.463
I am "We the people."

01:16:32.473 --> 01:16:33.499
We all are.

01:16:36.413 --> 01:16:37.423
We all are.

01:16:48.441 --> 01:16:50.440
I can't believe how I missed this.

01:16:54.468 --> 01:16:57.424
Wait, where you going?
We got a plane to catch.

01:16:57.492 --> 01:16:59.432
I'll be back in five minutes.

01:17:05.496 --> 01:17:08.452
JACKSON: My daddy used to fly airplanes.

01:17:08.463 --> 01:17:10.443
He wore the same as you.

01:17:11.447 --> 01:17:13.403
He's in heaven now.

01:17:16.444 --> 01:17:17.443
I see.

01:17:21.428 --> 01:17:22.487
You must miss him terribly.

01:17:25.422 --> 01:17:27.481
If he could be with you, he would.

01:17:27.488 --> 01:17:29.482
This I know.

01:17:29.489 --> 01:17:31.432
How do you know?

01:17:31.439 --> 01:17:35.448
Because everyfather
will always choose his child over...

01:17:39.490 --> 01:17:43.486
I would go to heaven
so Daddy could come back for Mommy.

01:17:43.497 --> 01:17:44.496
No, child.

01:17:46.420 --> 01:17:47.497
You mustn't say such a thing.

01:17:49.407 --> 01:17:51.406
That is an evil and pointless wish.

01:17:51.417 --> 01:17:53.414
But Mommy's always so sad.

01:17:53.421 --> 01:17:55.441
That's because she's forgotten
that our lives...

01:17:58.408 --> 01:17:59.434
belong to God.

01:18:00.492 --> 01:18:04.472
We must trust that God knows best.

01:18:06.442 --> 01:18:10.488
Do you really think
your mom would be less sad without you?

01:18:14.490 --> 01:18:16.433
She loves you.

01:18:19.434 --> 01:18:20.450
She needs you.

01:18:26.418 --> 01:18:27.437
MEREDITH: Jackson?

01:18:29.428 --> 01:18:31.484
Time to go home. Almost your bedtime.

01:19:11.492 --> 01:19:16.442
BENSON:<i> You feel that you're making
a last-ditch stand to protect your faith.</i>

01:19:18.406 --> 01:19:19.422
Don't you get it?

01:19:19.430 --> 01:19:22.416
<i>We've already decided what we're gonna do.</i>

01:19:22.427 --> 01:19:24.450
<i>"Laus Deo,</i>" it means praise be to God.

01:19:24.460 --> 01:19:27.466
America is a country so blessed
with prosperity.

01:19:27.477 --> 01:19:29.460
Religion has been removed from our schools.

01:19:29.467 --> 01:19:31.440
MARTIN:<i> "We the people
of the United States."</i>

01:19:31.447 --> 01:19:32.481
REBECCA:<i> "And secure
the blessings of liberty."</i>

01:19:32.491 --> 01:19:35.407
-ATTENDEE 2:<i> We're stronger together.</i>
-ATTENDEE 3:<i> I am "We the people."</i>

01:19:35.415 --> 01:19:36.414
ROBERT:<i> We all are.</i>

01:19:36.425 --> 01:19:37.424
SMITH:<i> "Don't worry
about what you will say.</i>

01:19:37.431 --> 01:19:39.444
"At the time,
you will be given what to say."

01:19:39.452 --> 01:19:40.478
DAVID:<i> "For it will not be you speaking,</i>

01:19:40.485 --> 01:19:45.402
"but the Spirit of your Father
speaking through you."

01:20:14.432 --> 01:20:17.405
Mr. Chairman, I would like to yield
my time to the witness...

01:20:19.406 --> 01:20:20.422
Reverend David Hill.

01:20:21.446 --> 01:20:22.445
That's fine,

01:20:22.453 --> 01:20:25.479
but I remind the witness
he's limited to five minutes.

01:20:33.400 --> 01:20:33.499
(CLEARS THROAT)

01:20:37.454 --> 01:20:38.497
(SIGHS)

01:20:40.468 --> 01:20:41.498
(MONITOR BEEPING)

01:20:42.405 --> 01:20:44.464
DAVID:<i> Thank you, Congressman Smith,</i>
<i>Mr. Chairman,</i>

01:20:46.402 --> 01:20:47.488
<i>for allowing me these last five minutes.</i>

01:20:52.492 --> 01:20:54.482
You ever been on one
of those sightseeing tours

01:20:54.489 --> 01:20:56.448
they have here in Washington?

01:20:57.493 --> 01:21:01.442
You know the kind where they take you
to see all the monuments?

01:21:01.453 --> 01:21:05.406
Yes, I believe most of us have visited
the city's major attractions.

01:21:06.477 --> 01:21:07.483
Baba.

01:21:11.407 --> 01:21:13.457
DAVID:<i> Maybe you ought to think
about going again,</i>

01:21:13.468 --> 01:21:16.444
cause those... how did you put that?

01:21:16.455 --> 01:21:21.495
Um, attractions are here for a reason,

01:21:23.429 --> 01:21:24.478
and I almost missed it.

01:21:26.402 --> 01:21:28.405
<i>I don't know how, because
you can't throw a rock in this city</i>

01:21:28.412 --> 01:21:30.425
<i>without hitting a statue
or a monument of some kind.</i>

01:21:30.436 --> 01:21:34.453
I mean, every street,
every building in this city,

01:21:34.460 --> 01:21:36.403
all the marble and the granite,

01:21:36.410 --> 01:21:39.490
the brick and the stone,
they're trying to tell us something.

01:21:40.494 --> 01:21:44.443
They're saying, "Don't forget about us.

01:21:46.431 --> 01:21:49.407
"Don't forget about
the battles that we fought

01:21:49.415 --> 01:21:51.471
"and the price that we paid for freedom.

01:21:52.462 --> 01:21:54.488
"Don't let our sacrifice be in vain."

01:21:57.422 --> 01:21:59.462
You wanna hear something interesting,
Mr. Chairman?

01:22:00.466 --> 01:22:03.413
I have three friends
that have a pretty good understanding

01:22:03.423 --> 01:22:05.406
of what's at stake here today,

01:22:06.490 --> 01:22:10.406
and the funny thing is,
is they're not even from America.

01:22:11.447 --> 01:22:18.414
They're from faraway places
like China, Iran, Africa.

01:22:22.408 --> 01:22:23.427
But they get it.

01:22:25.401 --> 01:22:26.485
They know what's at stake here.

01:22:27.495 --> 01:22:32.451
And maybe in order to understand how
precious and fragile freedom really is,

01:22:32.462 --> 01:22:33.492
maybe...

01:22:36.419 --> 01:22:37.479
maybe you have to lose it.

01:22:40.413 --> 01:22:41.429
But you already know that.

01:22:41.436 --> 01:22:45.470
I mean all of this,
it's just a distraction.

01:22:45.480 --> 01:22:48.420
And I made it easy for you, didn't I?

01:22:48.430 --> 01:22:50.403
I bet your face just lit up

01:22:50.414 --> 01:22:53.411
when you realized that there was a pastor
on the witness list.

01:22:53.418 --> 01:22:55.481
You knew that if you challenged scriptures,

01:22:55.488 --> 01:22:57.468
I would rise to defend them.

01:22:57.478 --> 01:22:59.487
It's kind of in my job description.

01:22:59.498 --> 01:23:01.445
You figured you'd run out the clock

01:23:01.452 --> 01:23:05.468
while we debated how women
wore their hair 2,000 years ago,

01:23:05.479 --> 01:23:08.419
all in hopes that no one would realize

01:23:08.429 --> 01:23:10.402
that it's really their freedoms
that are on the line.

01:23:10.413 --> 01:23:11.472
Not at all, sir.

01:23:11.483 --> 01:23:13.463
The issue here today is homeschooling.

01:23:13.470 --> 01:23:15.422
I wish it was, Mr. Chairman.

01:23:15.473 --> 01:23:16.486
I truly do.

01:23:16.497 --> 01:23:18.420
No, today...

01:23:19.430 --> 01:23:21.464
Today was about turning
neighbor against neighbor.

01:23:22.434 --> 01:23:24.431
That's part of your plan, isn't it?

01:23:24.437 --> 01:23:26.440
Keep us all divided.

01:23:26.451 --> 01:23:28.491
So bit by bit, we don't realize

01:23:29.401 --> 01:23:31.464
you're chipping away
at our freedoms and liberties.

01:23:31.471 --> 01:23:34.491
You got us all talking about how Noah
got all the animals on the ark.

01:23:35.402 --> 01:23:37.415
Meanwhile, you're crafting legislation

01:23:37.422 --> 01:23:40.425
that will allow the government
to barge into our homes.

01:23:41.436 --> 01:23:43.433
Because it's all about power for you.

01:23:43.439 --> 01:23:45.466
And the only way that
you can get more power

01:23:45.473 --> 01:23:47.482
is by taking it from someone else.

01:23:47.490 --> 01:23:50.437
And that would be all well and good
if it wasn't for that pesky thing

01:23:50.443 --> 01:23:52.473
called the Constitution that keeps
getting in your way.

01:23:52.484 --> 01:23:53.486
Now you hold on a second.

01:23:53.494 --> 01:23:55.457
No, I'm done talking to you!

01:23:55.467 --> 01:23:58.407
I'm talking to the people who elected you.

01:23:58.417 --> 01:24:02.477
Because as inconvenient as it is, sir,
this is where your power comes from!

01:24:03.461 --> 01:24:04.474
-Order!
-You see those statues

01:24:04.485 --> 01:24:06.425
and those monuments out there?

01:24:06.435 --> 01:24:09.484
They say, "You work for us!"

01:24:10.455 --> 01:24:12.445
You are out of order, Mr. Hill.

01:24:12.456 --> 01:24:16.489
A government of the people,
by the people, for the people.

01:24:19.476 --> 01:24:23.410
Order! You are out of order, Mr. Hill.

01:24:24.490 --> 01:24:26.437
Order!

01:24:26.444 --> 01:24:27.443
Bailiff.

01:24:30.461 --> 01:24:32.454
So stay out of our homes and churches,

01:24:32.461 --> 01:24:35.424
and, yes, stay out
of our children's education.

01:24:35.478 --> 01:24:38.415
Because what you call teaching,
Mr. Chairman,

01:24:38.465 --> 01:24:40.448
is really social engineering.

01:24:40.458 --> 01:24:42.438
You are out of order, Mr. Hill!

01:24:42.445 --> 01:24:43.461
History is being rewritten.

01:24:43.472 --> 01:24:47.499
Biology is redefined
and right and wrong are erased.

01:24:48.459 --> 01:24:51.425
Our children don't belong to the government

01:24:51.433 --> 01:24:53.432
and neither does our country.

01:24:53.443 --> 01:24:57.489
America belongs to its citizens,
to each and all.

01:24:57.497 --> 01:25:01.463
From the farmers in Texas to
the window cleaners in New York,

01:25:01.474 --> 01:25:05.400
to the cabinet makers in Maine
and the teachers in Oklahoma,

01:25:05.411 --> 01:25:08.424
to every man, woman and child,

01:25:08.431 --> 01:25:09.494
it belongs to the people!

01:25:12.458 --> 01:25:15.452
We the people.

01:25:23.449 --> 01:25:25.412
RONALD REAGAN:
<i>Freedom is a fragile thing.</i>

01:25:26.476 --> 01:25:30.460
<i>It must be fought for and defended
constantly by each generation.</i>

